{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["44-ACT-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "ACT"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Acts \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Acts of the Apostles \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Acts \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Act \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["The Acts of the Apostles \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 1:1"}, "The first book I wrote, Theophilus, concerned all that Isa began both to do and to teach,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 1:2"}, "until the day in which he was received up, after he had given commandment through the Holy Spirit to the apostles whom he\nhad chosen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 1:3"}, "To these he also showed himself alive after he suffered, by many proofs, appearing to them over a period of forty days,\nand speaking about Allah\u2019s Kingdom. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 1:4"}, "Being assembled together with them, he commanded them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t depart from Jerusalem, but wait for the promise of the\nFather, which you heard from me. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 1:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For Yahya indeed baptised in water, but you will be baptised in the Holy Spirit not many days from\nnow.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 1:6"}, "Therefore when they had come together, they asked him, \u201cLord, are you now restoring the kingdom to Israel?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 1:7"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt isn\u2019t for you to know times or seasons which the Father has set within his own authority.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 1:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you. You will be witnesses to me in Jerusalem, in all\nJudea and Samaria, and to the uttermost parts of the earth.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 1:9"}, "When he had said these things, as they were looking, he was taken up, and a cloud received him out of their sight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 1:10"}, "While they were looking steadfastly into the sky as he went,\nbehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " two men stood by them in white clothing, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 1:11"}, "who also said, \u201cYou men of Galilee, why do you stand looking into the sky? This Isa, who was received up from you into\nthe sky, will come back in the same way as you saw him going into the sky.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 1:12"}, "Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mountain called Olivet, which is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day\u2019s journey away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 1:13"}, "When they had come in, they went up into the upper room where they were staying; that is Peter, Yuhanna, Yaqub, Andreas,\nPhilip, Tau\u2019ma, Bar-Talmai, Matti, Yaqub the son of Alphaeus, Shima\u2019un the Zealot, and Yehuda the son of Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 1:14"}, "All these with one accord continued steadfastly in prayer and supplication, along with the women, and Maryam the mother\nof Isa, and with his brothers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 1:15"}, "In these days, Peter stood up in the middle of the disciples (and the number of names was about one hundred and twenty),\nand said, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 1:16"}, "\u201cBrothers, it was necessary that this Scripture should be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit spoke before by the mouth of\nDawood concerning Yehuda, who was guide to those who took Isa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 1:17"}, "For he was counted with us, and received his portion in this ministry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 1:18"}, "Now this man obtained a field with the reward for his wickedness, and falling headlong, his body burst open, and all his\nintestines gushed out. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 1:19"}, "It became known to everyone who lived in Jerusalem that in their language that field was called \u2018Akeldama,\u2019 that is, \u2018The\nfield of blood.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 1:20"}, "For it is written in the book of Zabur, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Let his habitation be made desolate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let no one dwell in it;\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 69:25"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["and, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Let another take his office.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 109:8"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 1:21"}, "\u201cOf the men therefore who have accompanied us all the time that the Lord Isa went in and out amongst us,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 1:22"}, "beginning from the baptism of Yahya, to the day that he was received up from us, of these one must become a witness with\nus of his resurrection.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 1:23"}, "They put forward two, Yusuf called Barsabbas, who was also called Justus, and Matthias.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 1:24"}, "They prayed and said, \u201cYou, Lord, who know the hearts of all men, show which one of these two you have chosen\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 1:25"}, "to take part in this ministry and apostleship from which Yehuda fell away, that he might go to his own place.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 1:26"}, "They drew lots for them, and the lot fell on Matthias, and he was counted with the eleven apostles.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 2:1"}, "Now when the day of Pentecost had come, they were all with one accord in one place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 2:2"}, "Suddenly there came from the sky a sound like the rushing of a mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were\nsitting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 2:3"}, "Tongues like fire appeared and were distributed to them, and one sat on each of them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 2:4"}, "They were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak with other languages, as the Spirit gave them the ability to\nspeak. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 2:5"}, "Now there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men, from every nation under the sky.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 2:6"}, "When this sound was heard, the multitude came together and were bewildered, because everyone heard them speaking in his\nown language. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 2:7"}, "They were all amazed and marvelled, saying to one another, \u201cBehold, aren\u2019t all these who speak Galileans?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 2:8"}, "How do we hear, everyone in our own native language? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 2:9"}, "Parthians, Medes, Elamites, and people from Mesopotamia, Judea, Cappadocia, Pontus, Asia,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 2:10"}, "Phrygia, Pamphylia, Egypt, the parts of Libya around Cyrene, visitors from Rome, both Jews and proselytes,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 2:11"}, "Cretans and Arabians: we hear them speaking in our languages the mighty works of Allah!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 2:12"}, "They were all amazed, and were perplexed, saying to one another, \u201cWhat does this mean?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 2:13"}, "Others, mocking, said, \u201cThey are filled with new wine.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 2:14"}, "But Peter, standing up with the eleven, lifted up his voice, and spoke out to them, \u201cYou men of Judea, and all you who\ndwell at Jerusalem, let this be known to you, and listen to my words.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 2:15"}, "For these aren\u2019t drunken, as you suppose, seeing it is only the third hour of the\nday.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["about 9:00 a.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 2:16"}, "But this is what has been spoken through the prophet Joel:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 2:17"}, "\u2018It will be in the last days, says Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Your sons and your daughters will prophesy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your young men will see visions. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your old men will dream dreams. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 2:18"}, "Yes, and on my servants and on my handmaidens in those days,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will pour out my Spirit, and they will prophesy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 2:19"}, "I will show wonders in the sky above, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and signs on the earth beneath: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["blood, and fire, and billows of smoke. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 2:20"}, "The sun will be turned into darkness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the moon into blood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["before the great and glorious day of the Lord comes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 2:21"}, "It will be that whoever will call on the name of the Lord will be\nsaved.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Joel 2:28-32"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 2:22"}, "\u201cMen of Israel, hear these words! Isa of Nazareth, a man approved by Allah to you by mighty works and wonders and signs\nwhich Allah did by him amongst you, even as you yourselves know,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 2:23"}, "him, being delivered up by the determined counsel and foreknowledge of Allah, you have taken by the hand of lawless men,\ncrucified and killed; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 2:24"}, "whom Allah raised up, having freed him from the agony of death, because it was not possible that he should be held by it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 2:25"}, "For Dawood says concerning him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018I saw the Lord always before my face, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for he is on my right hand, that I should not be moved. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 2:26"}, "Therefore my heart was glad, and my tongue rejoiced. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Moreover my flesh also will dwell in hope; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 2:27"}, "because you will not leave my soul in Hades,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:27\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither will you allow your Holy One to see decay. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 2:28"}, "You made known to me the ways of life. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will make me full of gladness with your presence.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:28\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 16:8-11 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 2:29"}, "\u201cBrothers, I may tell you freely of the patriarch Dawood, that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with us to\nthis day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 2:30"}, "Therefore, being a prophet, and knowing that Allah had sworn with an oath to him that of the fruit of his body, according\nto the flesh, he would raise up the Masih to sit on his throne, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 2:31"}, "he foreseeing this spoke about the resurrection of the Masih, that his soul wasn\u2019t left in\nHades,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and his flesh didn\u2019t see decay.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 2:32"}, "This Isa Allah raised up, to which we all are witnesses. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 2:33"}, "Being therefore exalted by the right hand of Allah, and having received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit,\nhe has poured out this, which you now see and hear. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 2:34"}, "For Dawood didn\u2019t ascend into the heavens, but he says himself,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018The Lord said to my Lord, \u201cSit by my right hand \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 2:35"}, "until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.\u201d\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:35 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 110:1 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 2:36"}, "\u201cLet all the house of Israel therefore know certainly that Allah has made him both Lord and Masih, this Isa whom you\ncrucified.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 2:37"}, "Now when they heard this, they were cut to the heart, and said to Peter and the rest of the apostles, \u201cBrothers, what\nshall we do?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 2:38"}, "Peter said to them, \u201cRepent, and be baptised, every one of you, in the name of Al Masih Isa for the forgiveness of sins,\nand you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 2:39"}, "For the promise is to you, and to your children, and to all who are far off, even as many as the Lord our Allah will call\nto himself.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 2:40"}, "With many other words he testified, and exhorted them, saying, \u201cSave yourselves from this crooked generation!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 2:41"}, "Then those who gladly received his word were baptised. There were added that day about three thousand souls.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 2:42"}, "They continued steadfastly in the apostles\u2019 teaching and fellowship, in the breaking of bread, and prayer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "ACT 2:43"}, "Fear came on every soul, and many wonders and signs were done through the apostles.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "ACT 2:44"}, "All who believed were together, and had all things in common.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "ACT 2:45"}, "They sold their possessions and goods, and distributed them to all, according as anyone had need.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "ACT 2:46"}, "Day by day, continuing steadfastly with one accord in the temple, and breaking bread at home, they took their food with\ngladness and singleness of heart, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "ACT 2:47"}, "praising Allah, and having favour with all the people. The Lord added to the assembly day by day those who were being\nsaved. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 3:1"}, "Peter and Yuhanna were going up into the temple at the hour of prayer, the ninth\nhour.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["3:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 3:2"}, "A certain man who was lame from his mother\u2019s womb was being carried, whom they laid daily at the door of the temple which\nis called Beautiful, to ask gifts for the needy of those who entered into the temple.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 3:3"}, "Seeing Peter and Yuhanna about to go into the temple, he asked to receive gifts for the needy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 3:4"}, "Peter, fastening his eyes on him, with Yuhanna, said, \u201cLook at us.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 3:5"}, "He listened to them, expecting to receive something from them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 3:6"}, "But Peter said, \u201cI have no silver or gold, but what I have, that I give you. In the name of Al Masih Isa of Nazareth, get\nup and walk!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 3:7"}, "He took him by the right hand and raised him up. Immediately his feet and his ankle bones received strength.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 3:8"}, "Leaping up, he stood and began to walk. He entered with them into the temple, walking, leaping, and praising Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 3:9"}, "All the people saw him walking and praising Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 3:10"}, "They recognised him, that it was he who used to sit begging for gifts for the needy at the Beautiful Gate of the temple.\nThey were filled with wonder and amazement at what had happened to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 3:11"}, "As the lame man who was healed held on to Peter and Yuhanna, all the people ran together to them in the porch that is\ncalled Sulaiman\u2019s, greatly wondering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 3:12"}, "When Peter saw it, he responded to the people, \u201cYou men of Israel, why do you marvel at this man? Why do you fasten your\neyes on us, as though by our own power or godliness we had made him walk?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 3:13"}, "The Allah of Ibrahim, Is\u1e25\u0101q, and Yaqub, Allah of our fathers, has glorified his Servant Isa, whom you delivered up, and\ndenied in the presence of Pilate, when he had determined to release him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 3:14"}, "But you denied the Holy and Righteous One and asked for a murderer to be granted to you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 3:15"}, "and killed the Prince of life, whom Allah raised from the dead, to which we are witnesses.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 3:16"}, "By faith in his name, his name has made this man strong, whom you see and know. Yes, the faith which is through him has\ngiven him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 3:17"}, "\u201cNow, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here may be also correctly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or\n\u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " I know that you did this in ignorance, as did also your rulers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 3:18"}, "But the things which Allah announced by the mouth of all his prophets, that Masih should suffer, he thus fulfilled.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 3:19"}, "\u201cRepent therefore, and turn again, that your sins may be blotted out, so that there may come times of refreshing from the\npresence of the Lord, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 3:20"}, "and that he may send Masih Isa, who was ordained for you before,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 3:21"}, "whom heaven must receive until the times of restoration of all things, which Allah spoke long ago by the mouth of his\nholy prophets. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 3:22"}, "For Musa indeed said to the fathers, \u2018The Lord Allah will raise up a prophet for you from amongst your brothers, like me.\nYou shall listen to him in all things whatever he says to you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 3:23"}, "It will be that every soul that will not listen to that prophet will be utterly destroyed from amongst the\npeople.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 18:15,18-19 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 3:24"}, "Yes, and all the prophets from Samuel and those who followed after, as many as have spoken, they also told of these days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 3:25"}, "You are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which Allah made with our fathers, saying to Ibrahim, \u2018All the\nfamilies of the earth will be blessed through your offspring.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 22:18; 26:4"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 3:26"}, "Allah, having raised up his servant Isa, sent him to you first to bless you, in turning away every one of you from your\nwickedness.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 4:1"}, "As they spoke to the people, the priests and the captain of the temple and the Sadducees came to them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 4:2"}, "being upset because they taught the people and proclaimed in Isa the resurrection from the dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 4:3"}, "They laid hands on them, and put them in custody until the next day, for it was now evening.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 4:4"}, "But many of those who heard the word believed, and the number of the men came to be about five thousand.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 4:5"}, "In the morning, their rulers, elders, and scribes were gathered together in Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 4:6"}, "Annas the high priest was there, with Caiaphas, Yuhanna, Alexander, and as many as were relatives of the high priest.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 4:7"}, "When they had stood Peter and Yuhanna in the middle of them, they enquired, \u201cBy what power, or in what name, have you done\nthis?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 4:8"}, "Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, \u201cYou rulers of the people, and elders of Israel,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 4:9"}, "if we are examined today concerning a good deed done to a crippled man, by what means this man has been healed,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 4:10"}, "may it be known to you all, and to all the people of Israel, that in the name of Al Masih Isa of Nazareth, whom you\ncrucified, whom Allah raised from the dead, this man stands here before you whole in him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 4:11"}, "He is \u2018the stone which was regarded as worthless by you, the builders, which has become the head of the\ncorner.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 118:22"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 4:12"}, "There is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven that is given amongst men, by which we must be\nsaved!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 4:13"}, "Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and Yuhanna, and had perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they\nmarvelled. They recognised that they had been with Isa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 4:14"}, "Seeing the man who was healed standing with them, they could say nothing against it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 4:15"}, "But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council, they conferred amongst themselves,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 4:16"}, "saying, \u201cWhat shall we do to these men? Because indeed a notable miracle has been done through them, as can be plainly\nseen by all who dwell in Jerusalem, and we can\u2019t deny it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 4:17"}, "But so that this spreads no further amongst the people, let\u2019s threaten them, that from now on they don\u2019t speak to anyone\nin this name.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 4:18"}, "They called them, and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 4:19"}, "But Peter and Yuhanna answered them, \u201cWhether it is right in the sight of Allah to listen to you rather than to Allah,\njudge for yourselves, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 4:20"}, "for we can\u2019t help telling the things which we saw and heard.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 4:21"}, "When they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding no way to punish them, because of the people; for\neveryone glorified Allah for that which was done. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 4:22"}, "For the man on whom this miracle of healing was performed was more than forty years old.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 4:23"}, "Being let go, they came to their own company and reported all that the chief priests and the elders had said to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 4:24"}, "When they heard it, they lifted up their voice to Allah with one accord, and said, \u201cO Lord, you are Allah, who made the\nheaven, the earth, the sea, and all that is in them; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 4:25"}, "who by the mouth of your servant, Dawood, said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Why do the nations rage, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the peoples plot a vain thing? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 4:26"}, "The kings of the earth take a stand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the rulers take council together, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["against the Lord, and against his Masih.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["ChristGreek and Messiah (Hebrew) both mean Anointed\nOne."]}], "caller": "+"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 2:1-2"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 4:27"}, "\u201cFor truly,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["nu adds \u201cin this city,\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " both Herod and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles and the people\nof Israel, were gathered together against your holy servant, Isa, whom you anointed,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 4:28"}, "to do whatever your hand and your council foreordained to happen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 4:29"}, "Now, Lord, look at their threats, and grant to your servants to speak your word with all boldness,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 4:30"}, "while you stretch out your hand to heal; and that signs and wonders may be done through the name of your holy Servant\nIsa.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 4:31"}, "When they had prayed, the place was shaken where they were gathered together. They were all filled with the Holy Spirit,\nand they spoke the word of Allah with boldness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 4:32"}, "The multitude of those who believed were of one heart and soul. Not one of them claimed that anything of the things which\nhe possessed was his own, but they had all things in common. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 4:33"}, "With great power, the apostles gave their testimony of the resurrection of the Lord Isa. Great grace was on them all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 4:34"}, "For neither was there amongst them any who lacked, for as many as were owners of lands or houses sold them, and brought\nthe proceeds of the things that were sold, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 4:35"}, "and laid them at the apostles\u2019 feet, and distribution was made to each, according as anyone had need.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 4:36"}, "Joses, who by the apostles was also called Barnabas (which is, being interpreted, Son of Encouragement), a Levite, a man\nof Cyprus by race, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 4:37"}, "having a field, sold it and brought the money and laid it at the apostles\u2019 feet.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 5:1"}, "But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira, his wife, sold a possession,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 5:2"}, "and kept back part of the price, his wife also being aware of it, then brought a certain part and laid it at the apostles\u2019\nfeet. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 5:3"}, "But Peter said, \u201cAnanias, why has Iblis filled your heart to lie to the Holy Spirit and to keep back part of the price of\nthe land? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 5:4"}, "While you kept it, didn\u2019t it remain your own? After it was sold, wasn\u2019t it in your power? How is it that you have\nconceived this thing in your heart? You haven\u2019t lied to men, but to Allah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 5:5"}, "Ananias, hearing these words, fell down and died. Great fear came on all who heard these things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 5:6"}, "The young men arose and wrapped him up, and they carried him out and buried him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 5:7"}, "About three hours later, his wife, not knowing what had happened, came in.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 5:8"}, "Peter answered her, \u201cTell me whether you sold the land for so much.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cYes, for so much.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 5:9"}, "But Peter asked her, \u201cHow is it that you have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? Behold, the feet of those\nwho have buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 5:10"}, "She fell down immediately at his feet and died. The young men came in and found her dead, and they carried her out and\nburied her by her husband. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 5:11"}, "Great fear came on the whole assembly, and on all who heard these things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 5:12"}, "By the hands of the apostles many signs and wonders were done amongst the people. They were all with one accord in\nSulaiman\u2019s porch. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 5:13"}, "None of the rest dared to join them, however the people honoured them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 5:14"}, "More believers were added to the Lord, multitudes of both men and women.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 5:15"}, "They even carried out the sick into the streets, and laid them on cots and mattresses, so that as Peter came by, at the\nleast his shadow might overshadow some of them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 5:16"}, "The multitude also came together from the cities around Jerusalem, bringing sick people and those who were tormented by\nunclean spirits: and they were all healed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 5:17"}, "But the high priest rose up, and all those who were with him (which is the sect of the Sadducees), and they were filled\nwith jealousy \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 5:18"}, "and laid hands on the apostles, then put them in public custody.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 5:19"}, "But an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors by night, and brought them out and said,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 5:20"}, "\u201cGo stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 5:21"}, "When they heard this, they entered into the temple about daybreak and taught. But the high priest came, and those who\nwere with him, and called the council together, and all the senate of the children of Israel, and sent to the prison to have\nthem brought. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 5:22"}, "But the officers who came didn\u2019t find them in the prison. They returned and reported,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 5:23"}, "\u201cWe found the prison shut and locked, and the guards standing before the doors, but when we opened them, we found no one\ninside!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 5:24"}, "Now when the high priest, the captain of the temple, and the chief priests heard these words, they were very perplexed\nabout them and what might become of this. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 5:25"}, "One came and told them, \u201cBehold, the men whom you put in prison are in the temple, standing and teaching the people.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 5:26"}, "Then the captain went with the officers, and brought them without violence, for they were afraid that the people might\nstone them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 5:27"}, "When they had brought them, they set them before the council. The high priest questioned them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 5:28"}, "saying, \u201cDidn\u2019t we strictly command you not to teach in this name? Behold, you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching,\nand intend to bring this man\u2019s blood on us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 5:29"}, "But Peter and the apostles answered, \u201cWe must obey Allah rather than men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 5:30"}, "The Allah of our fathers raised up Isa, whom you killed, hanging him on a tree.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 5:31"}, "Allah exalted him with his right hand to be a Prince and a Saviour, to give repentance to Israel, and remission of sins.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 5:32"}, "We are his witnesses of these things; and so also is the Holy Spirit, whom Allah has given to those who obey him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 5:33"}, "But they, when they heard this, were cut to the heart, and were determined to kill them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 5:34"}, "But one stood up in the council, a Pharisee named Gamaliel, a teacher of the law, honoured by all the people, and\ncommanded to put the apostles out for a little while. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 5:35"}, "He said to them, \u201cYou men of Israel, be careful concerning these men, what you are about to do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 5:36"}, "For before these days Theudas rose up, making himself out to be somebody; to whom a number of men, about four hundred,\njoined themselves. He was slain; and all, as many as obeyed him, were dispersed, and came to nothing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 5:37"}, "After this man, Yehuda of Galilee rose up in the days of the enrolment, and drew away some people after him. He also\nperished, and all, as many as obeyed him, were scattered abroad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 5:38"}, "Now I tell you, withdraw from these men, and leave them alone. For if this counsel or this work is of men, it will be\noverthrown. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 5:39"}, "But if it is of Allah, you will not be able to overthrow it, and you would be found even to be fighting against Allah!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 5:40"}, "They agreed with him. Summoning the apostles, they beat them and commanded them not to speak in the name of Isa, and let\nthem go. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 5:41"}, "They therefore departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted worthy to suffer dishonour for\nIsa\u2019s name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 5:42"}, "Every day, in the temple and at home, they never stopped teaching and preaching Isa, the Masih.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 6:1"}, "Now in those days, when the number of the disciples was multiplying, a complaint arose from the\nHellenists", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hellenists used Greek language and culture, even though they were also of Hebrew\ndescent."]}], "caller": "+"}, " against the Hebrews, because their widows were neglected in the daily service.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 6:2"}, "The twelve summoned the multitude of the disciples and said, \u201cIt is not appropriate for us to forsake the word of Allah\nand serve tables. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 6:3"}, "Therefore select from amongst you, brothers, seven men of good report, full of the Holy Spirit and of wisdom, whom we may\nappoint over this business. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 6:4"}, "But we will continue steadfastly in prayer and in the ministry of the word.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 6:5"}, "These words pleased the whole multitude. They chose Stephen, a man full of faith and of the Holy Spirit, Philip,\nProchorus, Nicanor, Timon, Parmenas, and Nicolaus, a proselyte of Antioch;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 6:6"}, "whom they set before the apostles. When they had prayed, they laid their hands on them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 6:7"}, "The word of Allah increased and the number of the disciples greatly multiplied in Jerusalem. A great company of the\npriests were obedient to the faith. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 6:8"}, "Stephen, full of faith and power, performed great wonders and signs amongst the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 6:9"}, "But some of those who were of the synagogue called \u201cThe Libertines\u201d, and of the Cyrenians, of the Alexandrians, and of\nthose of Cilicia and Asia arose, disputing with Stephen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 6:10"}, "They weren\u2019t able to withstand the wisdom and the Spirit by which he spoke.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 6:11"}, "Then they secretly induced men to say, \u201cWe have heard him speak blasphemous words against Musa and Allah.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 6:12"}, "They stirred up the people, the elders, and the scribes, and came against him and seized him, then brought him in to the\ncouncil, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 6:13"}, "and set up false witnesses who said, \u201cThis man never stops speaking blasphemous words against this holy place and the\nlaw. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 6:14"}, "For we have heard him say that this Isa of Nazareth will destroy this place, and will change the customs which Musa\ndelivered to us.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 6:15"}, "All who sat in the council, fastening their eyes on him, saw his face like it was the face of an angel.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 7:1"}, "The high priest said, \u201cAre these things so?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 7:2"}, "He said, \u201cBrothers and fathers, listen. The Allah of glory appeared to our father Ibrahim when he was in Mesopotamia,\nbefore he lived in Haran, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 7:3"}, "and said to him, \u2018Get out of your land and away from your relatives, and come into a land which I will show\nyou.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 12:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 7:4"}, "Then he came out of the land of the Chaldaeans and lived in Haran. From there, when his father was dead, Allah moved him\ninto this land, where you are now living. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 7:5"}, "He gave him no inheritance in it, no, not so much as to set his foot on. He promised that he would give it to him for a\npossession, and to his offspring after him, when he still had no child.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 7:6"}, "Allah spoke in this way: that his offspring would live as aliens in a strange land, and that they would be enslaved and\nmistreated for four hundred years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 7:7"}, "\u2018I will judge the nation to which they will be in bondage,\u2019 said Allah, \u2018and after that they will come out, and serve me\nin this place.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 15:13-14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 7:8"}, "He gave him the covenant of circumcision. So Ibrahim became the father of Is\u1e25\u0101q, and circumcised him the eighth day. Is\u1e25\u0101q\nbecame the father of Yaqub, and Yaqub became the father of the twelve patriarchs.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 7:9"}, "\u201cThe patriarchs, moved with jealousy against Yusuf, sold him into Egypt. Allah was with him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 7:10"}, "and delivered him out of all his afflictions, and gave him favour and wisdom before Pharaoh, king of Egypt. He made him\ngovernor over Egypt and all his house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 7:11"}, "Now a famine came over all the land of Egypt and Canaan, and great affliction. Our fathers found no food.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 7:12"}, "But when Yaqub heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent out our fathers the first time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 7:13"}, "On the second time Yusuf was made known to his brothers, and Yusuf\u2019s race was revealed to Pharaoh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 7:14"}, "Yusuf sent and summoned Yaqub, his father, and all his relatives, seventy-five souls.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 7:15"}, "Yaqub went down into Egypt and he died, himself and our fathers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 7:16"}, "and they were brought back to Shechem, and laid in the tomb that Ibrahim bought for a price in silver from the children\nof Hamor of Shechem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 7:17"}, "\u201cBut as the time of the promise came close which Allah had sworn to Ibrahim, the people grew and multiplied in Egypt,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 7:18"}, "until there arose a different king, who didn\u2019t know Yusuf.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 7:19"}, "The same took advantage of our race, and mistreated our fathers, and forced them to throw out their babies, so that they\nwouldn\u2019t stay alive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 7:20"}, "At that time Musa was born, and was exceedingly handsome. He was nourished three months in his father\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 7:21"}, "When he was thrown out, Pharaoh\u2019s daughter took him up and reared him as her own son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 7:22"}, "Musa was instructed in all the wisdom of the Egyptians. He was mighty in his words and works.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 7:23"}, "But when he was forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his\nbrothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may be also correctly translated\n\u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 7:24"}, "Seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him who was oppressed, striking the Egyptian.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 7:25"}, "He supposed that his brothers understood that Allah, by his hand, was giving them deliverance; but they didn\u2019t\nunderstand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 7:26"}, "\u201cThe day following, he appeared to them as they fought, and urged them to be at peace again, saying, \u2018Sirs, you are\nbrothers. Why do you wrong one another?\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 7:27"}, "But he who did his neighbour wrong pushed him away, saying, \u2018Who made you a ruler and a judge over us?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 7:28"}, "Do you want to kill me, as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 2:14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 7:29"}, "Musa fled at this saying, and became a stranger in the land of Midian, where he became the father of two sons.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 7:30"}, "\u201cWhen forty years were fulfilled, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in the wilderness of Mount Sinai, in a flame of\nfire in a bush. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 7:31"}, "When Musa saw it, he wondered at the sight. As he came close to see, a voice of the Lord came to him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 7:32"}, "\u2018I am Allah of your fathers, Allah of Ibrahim, Allah of Is\u1e25\u0101q, and Allah of\nYaqub.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 3:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Musa trembled, and dared not look.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 7:33"}, "The Lord said to him, \u2018Take off your sandals, for the place where you stand is holy ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 7:34"}, "I have surely seen the affliction of my people that is in Egypt, and have heard their groaning. I have come down to\ndeliver them. Now come, I will send you into Egypt.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:34\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 3:5,7-8,10"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 7:35"}, "\u201cThis Musa, whom they refused, saying, \u2018Who made you a ruler and a judge?\u2019\u2014Allah has sent him as both a ruler and a\ndeliverer by the hand of the angel who appeared to him in the bush.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 7:36"}, "This man led them out, having worked wonders and signs in Egypt, in the Red Sea, and in the wilderness for forty years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 7:37"}, "This is that Musa, who said to the children of Israel, \u2018The Lord our Allah will raise up a prophet for you from amongst\nyour brothers, like me.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:37 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cYou shall listen to\nhim.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:37 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 18:15"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 7:38"}, "This is he who was in the assembly in the wilderness with the angel that spoke to him on Mount Sinai, and with our\nfathers, who received living revelations to give to us, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 7:39"}, "to whom our fathers wouldn\u2019t be obedient, but rejected him, and turned back in their hearts to Egypt,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 7:40"}, "saying to Harun, \u2018Make us gods that will go before us, for as for this Musa, who led us out of the land of Egypt, we\ndon\u2019t know what has become of him.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:40 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 32:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 7:41"}, "They made a calf in those days, and brought a sacrifice to the idol, and rejoiced in the works of their hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 7:42"}, "But Allah turned, and gave them up to serve the army of the\nsky,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:42 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["This idiom could also be translated \u201chost of heaven\u201d, or \u201cangelic beings\u201d, or \u201cheavenly\nbodies.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " as it is written in the book of the prophets, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Did you offer to me slain animals and sacrifices \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["forty years in the wilderness, O house of Israel? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "ACT 7:43"}, "You took up the tabernacle of Moloch, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the star of your god Rephan, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["the figures which you made to worship. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will carry you away", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:43 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Amos 5:25-27"]}], "caller": "+"}, " beyond Babylon.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "ACT 7:44"}, "\u201cOur fathers had the tabernacle of the testimony in the wilderness, even as he who spoke to Musa commanded him to make it\naccording to the pattern that he had seen; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "ACT 7:45"}, "which also our fathers, in their turn, brought in with Joshua when they entered into the possession of the nations, whom\nAllah drove out before the face of our fathers, to the days of Dawood,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "ACT 7:46"}, "who found favour in the sight of Allah, and asked to find a habitation for Allah of Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "ACT 7:47"}, "But Sulaiman built him a house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "ACT 7:48"}, "However, the Most High doesn\u2019t dwell in temples made with hands, as the prophet says,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "ACT 7:49"}, "\u2018heaven is my throne, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the earth a footstool for my feet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["What kind of house will you build me?\u2019 says the Lord. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018Or what is the place of my rest? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "ACT 7:50"}, "Didn\u2019t my hand make all these things?\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:50 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n66:1-2"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "ACT 7:51"}, "\u201cYou stiff-necked and uncircumcised in heart and ears, you always resist the Holy Spirit! As your fathers did, so you do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "ACT 7:52"}, "Which of the prophets didn\u2019t your fathers persecute? They killed those who foretold the coming of the Righteous One, of\nwhom you have now become betrayers and murderers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "ACT 7:53"}, "You received the law as it was ordained by angels, and didn\u2019t keep it!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "ACT 7:54"}, "Now when they heard these things, they were cut to the heart, and they gnashed at him with their teeth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "ACT 7:55"}, "But he, being full of the Holy Spirit, looked up steadfastly into heaven and saw the glory of Allah, and Isa standing on\nthe right hand of Allah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "ACT 7:56"}, "and said, \u201cBehold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of Man standing at the right hand of Allah!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "ACT 7:57"}, "But they cried out with a loud voice and stopped their ears, then rushed at him with one accord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "ACT 7:58"}, "They threw him out of the city and stoned him. The witnesses placed their garments at the feet of a young man named Saul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "ACT 7:59"}, "They stoned Stephen as he called out, saying, \u201cLord Isa, receive my spirit!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "ACT 7:60"}, "He knelt down, and cried with a loud voice, \u201cLord, don\u2019t hold this sin against them!\u201d When he had said this, he fell\nasleep. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 8:1"}, "Saul was consenting to his death. A great persecution arose against the assembly which was in Jerusalem in that day. They\nwere all scattered abroad throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria, except for the apostles.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 8:2"}, "Devout men buried Stephen and lamented greatly over him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 8:3"}, "But Saul ravaged the assembly, entering into every house and dragged both men and women off to prison.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 8:4"}, "Therefore those who were scattered abroad went around preaching the word.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 8:5"}, "Philip went down to the city of Samaria, and proclaimed to them the Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 8:6"}, "The multitudes listened with one accord to the things that were spoken by Philip when they heard and saw the signs which\nhe did. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 8:7"}, "For unclean spirits came out of many of those who had them. They came out, crying with a loud voice. Many who had been\nparalysed and lame were healed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 8:8"}, "There was great joy in that city. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 8:9"}, "But there was a certain man, Shima\u2019un by name, who used to practise sorcery in the city and amazed the people of Samaria,\nmaking himself out to be some great one, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 8:10"}, "to whom they all listened, from the least to the greatest, saying, \u201cThis man is that great power of Allah.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 8:11"}, "They listened to him, because for a long time he had amazed them with his sorceries.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 8:12"}, "But when they believed Philip preaching good news concerning Allah\u2019s Kingdom and the name of Al Masih Isa, they were\nbaptised, both men and women. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 8:13"}, "Shima\u2019un himself also believed. Being baptised, he continued with Philip. Seeing signs and great miracles occurring, he\nwas amazed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 8:14"}, "Now when the apostles who were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of Allah, they sent Peter and\nYuhanna to them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 8:15"}, "who, when they had come down, prayed for them, that they might receive the Holy Spirit;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 8:16"}, "for as yet he had fallen on none of them. They had only been baptised in the name of Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 8:17"}, "Then they laid their hands on them, and they received the Holy Spirit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 8:18"}, "Now when Shima\u2019un saw that the Holy Spirit was given through the laying on of the apostles\u2019 hands, he offered them money,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 8:19"}, "saying, \u201cGive me also this power, that whomever I lay my hands on may receive the Holy Spirit.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 8:20"}, "But Peter said to him, \u201cMay your silver perish with you, because you thought you could obtain the gift of Allah with\nmoney! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 8:21"}, "You have neither part nor lot in this matter, for your heart isn\u2019t right before Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 8:22"}, "Repent therefore of this, your wickedness, and ask Allah if perhaps the thought of your heart may be forgiven you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 8:23"}, "For I see that you are in the poison of bitterness and in the bondage of iniquity.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 8:24"}, "Shima\u2019un answered, \u201cPray for me to the Lord, that none of the things which you have spoken happen to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 8:25"}, "They therefore, when they had testified and spoken the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem, and preached the Good\nNews to many villages of the Samaritans. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 8:26"}, "But an angel of the Lord spoke to Philip, saying, \u201cArise, and go towards the south to the way that goes down from\nJerusalem to Gaza. This is a desert.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 8:27"}, "He arose and went; and behold, there was a man of Ethiopia, a eunuch of great authority under Candace, queen of the\nEthiopians, who was over all her treasure, who had come to Jerusalem to worship.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 8:28"}, "He was returning and sitting in his chariot, and was reading the prophet Isaiah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 8:29"}, "The Spirit said to Philip, \u201cGo near, and join yourself to this chariot.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 8:30"}, "Philip ran to him, and heard him reading Isaiah the prophet, and said, \u201cDo you understand what you are reading?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 8:31"}, "He said, \u201cHow can I, unless someone explains it to me?\u201d He begged Philip to come up and sit with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 8:32"}, "Now the passage of the Scripture which he was reading was this,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHe was led as a sheep to the slaughter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["As a lamb before his shearer is silent, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so he doesn\u2019t open his mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 8:33"}, "In his humiliation, his judgement was taken away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who will declare His generation? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For his life is taken from the earth.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["8:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n53:7,8"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 8:34"}, "The eunuch answered Philip, \u201cWho is the prophet talking about? About himself, or about someone else?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 8:35"}, "Philip opened his mouth, and beginning from this Scripture, preached to him about Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 8:36"}, "As they went on the way, they came to some water, and the eunuch said, \u201cBehold, here is water. What is keeping me from\nbeing baptised?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 8:37"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:37 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "fqa", "content": ["Philip said, \u201cIf you believe with all your heart, you may.\u201d He answered, \u201cI believe that\nAl Masih Isa is the Son of Allah.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 8:38"}, "He commanded the chariot to stand still, and they both went down into the water, both Philip and the eunuch, and he\nbaptised him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 8:39"}, "When they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught Philip away, and the eunuch didn\u2019t see him any more,\nfor he went on his way rejoicing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 8:40"}, "But Philip was found at Azotus. Passing through, he preached the Good News to all the cities, until he came to Caesarea.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 9:1"}, "But Saul, still breathing threats and slaughter against the disciples of the Lord, went to the high priest\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 9:2"}, "and asked for letters from him to the synagogues of Damascus, that if he found any who were of the Way, whether men or\nwomen, he might bring them bound to Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 9:3"}, "As he travelled, he got close to Damascus, and suddenly a light from the sky shone around him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 9:4"}, "He fell on the earth, and heard a voice saying to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSaul, Saul, why do you persecute\nme?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 9:5"}, "He said, \u201cWho are you, Lord?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The Lord said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI am Isa, whom you are persecuting."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cIt\u2019s hard for you to kick against the cattle\nprods.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 9:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR omits \u201cBut\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["rise up and enter into the city, then you will be told what you must\ndo.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 9:7"}, "The men who travelled with him stood speechless, hearing the sound, but seeing no one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 9:8"}, "Saul arose from the ground, and when his eyes were opened, he saw no one. They led him by the hand, and brought him into\nDamascus. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 9:9"}, "He was without sight for three days, and neither ate nor drank.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 9:10"}, "Now there was a certain disciple at Damascus named Ananias. The Lord said to him in a vision,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAnanias!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cBehold, it\u2019s me, Lord.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 9:11"}, "The Lord said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cArise, and go to the street which is called Straight, and enquire in the house of\nJudah"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Yehuda"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for one named Saul, a man of Tarsus. For behold, he is praying,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 9:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and in a vision he has seen a man named Ananias coming in and laying his hands on him, that he might receive his\nsight.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 9:13"}, "But Ananias answered, \u201cLord, I have heard from many about this man, how much evil he did to your saints at Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 9:14"}, "Here he has authority from the chief priests to bind all who call on your name.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 9:15"}, "But the Lord said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo your way, for he is my chosen vessel to bear my name before the nations and kings, and\nthe children of Israel. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 9:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For I will show him how many things he must suffer for my name\u2019s\nsake.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 9:17"}, "Ananias departed and entered into the house. Laying his hands on him, he said, \u201cBrother Saul, the Lord, who appeared to\nyou on the road by which you came, has sent me that you may receive your sight and be filled with the Holy Spirit.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 9:18"}, "Immediately something like scales fell from his eyes, and he received his sight. He arose and was baptised.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 9:19"}, "He took food and was strengthened. Saul stayed several days with the disciples who were at Damascus.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 9:20"}, "Immediately in the synagogues he proclaimed the Masih, that he is the Son of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 9:21"}, "All who heard him were amazed, and said, \u201cIsn\u2019t this he who in Jerusalem made havoc of those who called on this name? And\nhe had come here intending to bring them bound before the chief priests!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 9:22"}, "But Saul increased more in strength, and confounded the Jews who lived at Damascus, proving that this is the Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 9:23"}, "When many days were fulfilled, the Jews conspired together to kill him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 9:24"}, "but their plot became known to Saul. They watched the gates both day and night that they might kill him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 9:25"}, "but his disciples took him by night and let him down through the wall, lowering him in a basket.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 9:26"}, "When Saul had come to Jerusalem, he tried to join himself to the disciples; but they were all afraid of him, not\nbelieving that he was a disciple. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 9:27"}, "But Barnabas took him and brought him to the apostles, and declared to them how he had seen the Lord on the way, and that\nhe had spoken to him, and how at Damascus he had preached boldly in the name of Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 9:28"}, "He was with them entering into", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR and NU add \u201cand going out\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Jerusalem, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 9:29"}, "preaching boldly in the name of the Lord Isa.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:29\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR and NU omit \u201cIsa\u201d and reverse the order of verses 28 & 29."]}], "caller": "+"}, " He spoke and disputed against the\nHellenists,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hellenists were Hebrews who used Greek language and\nculture."]}], "caller": "+"}, " but they were seeking to kill him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 9:30"}, "When the brothers", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " knew it, they brought him down to Caesarea, and sent him off to Tarsus.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 9:31"}, "So the assemblies throughout all Judea, Galilee, and Samaria had peace, and were built up. They were multiplied, walking\nin the fear of the Lord and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 9:32"}, "As Peter went throughout all those parts, he came down also to the saints who lived at Lydda.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 9:33"}, "There he found a certain man named Aeneas, who had been bedridden for eight years, because he was paralysed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 9:34"}, "Peter said to him, \u201cAeneas, Al Masih Isa heals you. Get up and make your bed!\u201d Immediately he arose.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 9:35"}, "All who lived at Lydda and in Sharon saw him, and they turned to the Lord.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 9:36"}, "Now there was at Joppa a certain disciple named Tabitha, which when translated, means\nDorcas.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cDorcas\u201d is Greek for \u201cGazelle.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " This woman was full of good works and acts of mercy which she\ndid. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 9:37"}, "In those days, she became sick, and died. When they had washed her, they laid her in an upper room.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 9:38"}, "As Lydda was near Joppa, the disciples, hearing that Peter was there, sent two\nmen", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:38 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Reading from NU, TR; MT omits \u201ctwo men\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " to him, imploring him not to delay in coming to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 9:39"}, "Peter got up and went with them. When he had come, they brought him into the upper room. All the widows stood by him\nweeping, and showing the coats and garments which Dorcas had made while she was with them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 9:40"}, "Peter sent them all out, and knelt down and prayed. Turning to the body, he said, \u201cTabitha, get up!\u201d She opened her eyes,\nand when she saw Peter, she sat up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 9:41"}, "He gave her his hand, and raised her up. Calling the saints and widows, he presented her alive.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 9:42"}, "This became known throughout all Joppa, and many believed in the Lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "ACT 9:43"}, "He stayed many days in Joppa with a tanner named Shima\u2019un.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 10:1"}, "Now there was a certain man in Caesarea, Cornelius by name, a centurion of what was called the Italian Regiment,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 10:2"}, "a devout man, and one who feared Allah with all his house, who gave gifts for the needy generously to the people, and\nalways prayed to Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 10:3"}, "At about the ninth hour of the day,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["3:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " he clearly saw in a vision an angel of Allah coming to\nhim, and saying to him, \u201cCornelius!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 10:4"}, "He, fastening his eyes on him, and being frightened, said, \u201cWhat is it, Lord?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cYour prayers and your gifts to the needy have gone up for a memorial before Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 10:5"}, "Now send men to Joppa, and get Shima\u2019un, who is also called Peter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 10:6"}, "He is staying with a tanner named Shima\u2019un, whose house is by the seaside.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cThis one will tell you what it is necessary for you to\ndo.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 10:7"}, "When the angel who spoke to him had departed, Cornelius called two of his household servants and a devout soldier of those\nwho waited on him continually. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 10:8"}, "Having explained everything to them, he sent them to Joppa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 10:9"}, "Now on the next day as they were on their journey, and got close to the city, Peter went up on the housetop to pray at\nabout noon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 10:10"}, "He became hungry and desired to eat, but while they were preparing, he fell into a trance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 10:11"}, "He saw heaven opened and a certain container descending to him, like a great sheet let down by four corners on the earth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 10:12"}, "in which were all kinds of four-footed animals of the earth, wild animals, reptiles, and birds of the sky.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 10:13"}, "A voice came to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cRise, Peter, kill and eat!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 10:14"}, "But Peter said, \u201cNot so, Lord; for I have never eaten anything that is common or unclean.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 10:15"}, "A voice came to him again the second time, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat Allah has cleansed, you must not call\nunclean.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 10:16"}, "This was done three times, and immediately the vessel was received up into heaven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 10:17"}, "Now while Peter was very perplexed in himself what the vision which he had seen might mean, behold, the men who were sent\nby Cornelius, having made enquiry for Shima\u2019un\u2019s house, stood before the gate,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 10:18"}, "and called and asked whether Shima\u2019un, who was also called Peter, was lodging there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 10:19"}, "While Peter was pondering the vision, the Spirit said to him, \u201cBehold, three\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Reading from TR and NU. MT omits \u201cthree\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " men seek you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 10:20"}, "But arise, get down, and go with them, doubting nothing; for I have sent them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 10:21"}, "Peter went down to the men, and said, \u201cBehold, I am he whom you seek. Why have you come?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 10:22"}, "They said, \u201cCornelius, a centurion, a righteous man and one who fears Allah, and well spoken of by all the nation of the\nJews, was directed by a holy angel to invite you to his house, and to listen to what you say.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 10:23"}, "So he called them in and provided a place to stay. On the next day Peter arose and went out with them, and some of the\nbrothers from Joppa accompanied him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 10:24"}, "On the next day they entered into Caesarea. Cornelius was waiting for them, having called together his relatives and his\nnear friends. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 10:25"}, "When Peter entered, Cornelius met him, fell down at his feet, and worshipped him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 10:26"}, "But Peter raised him up, saying, \u201cStand up! I myself am also a man.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 10:27"}, "As he talked with him, he went in and found many gathered together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 10:28"}, "He said to them, \u201cYou yourselves know how it is an unlawful thing for a man who is a Jew to join himself or come to one\nof another nation, but Allah has shown me that I shouldn\u2019t call any man unholy or unclean.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 10:29"}, "Therefore I also came without complaint when I was sent for. I ask therefore, why did you send for me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 10:30"}, "Cornelius said, \u201cFour days ago, I was fasting until this hour, and at the ninth\nhour,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["3:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I prayed in my house, and behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 10:31"}, "and said, \u2018Cornelius, your prayer is heard, and your gifts to the needy are remembered in the sight of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 10:32"}, "Send therefore to Joppa, and summon Shima\u2019un, who is also called Peter. He is staying in the house of a tanner named\nShima\u2019un, by the seaside. When he comes, he will speak to you.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 10:33"}, "Therefore I sent to you at once, and it was good of you to come. Now therefore we are all here present in the sight of\nAllah to hear all things that have been commanded you by Allah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 10:34"}, "Peter opened his mouth and said, \u201cTruly I perceive that Allah doesn\u2019t show favouritism;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 10:35"}, "but in every nation he who fears him and works righteousness is acceptable to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 10:36"}, "The word which he sent to the children of Israel, preaching good news of peace by Al Masih Isa\u2014he is Lord of all\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 10:37"}, "you yourselves know what happened, which was proclaimed throughout all Judea, beginning from Galilee, after the baptism\nwhich Yuhanna preached; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 10:38"}, "even Isa of Nazareth, how Allah anointed him with the Holy Spirit and with power, who went about doing good and healing\nall who were oppressed by the Iblis, for Allah was with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 10:39"}, "We are witnesses of everything he did both in the country of the Jews, and in Jerusalem; whom they\nalso", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:39 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR omits \u201calso\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " killed, hanging him on a tree.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 10:40"}, "Allah raised him up the third day, and gave him to be revealed,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 10:41"}, "not to all the people, but to witnesses who were chosen before by Allah, to us, who ate and drank with him after he rose\nfrom the dead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 10:42"}, "He commanded us to preach to the people and to testify that this is he who is appointed by Allah as the Judge of the\nliving and the dead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "ACT 10:43"}, "All the prophets testify about him, that through his name everyone who believes in him will receive remission of sins.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "ACT 10:44"}, "While Peter was still speaking these words, the Holy Spirit fell on all those who heard the word.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "ACT 10:45"}, "They of the circumcision who believed were amazed, as many as came with Peter, because the gift of the Holy Spirit was\nalso poured out on the Gentiles. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "ACT 10:46"}, "For they heard them speaking in other languages and magnifying Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Peter answered, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "ACT 10:47"}, "\u201cCan anyone forbid these people from being baptised with water? They have received the Holy Spirit just like us.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "ACT 10:48"}, "He commanded them to be baptised in the name of Al Masih Isa. Then they asked him to stay some days.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 11:1"}, "Now the apostles and the brothers", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be\ncorrectly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " who were in Judea heard that the Gentiles had also received the\nword of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 11:2"}, "When Peter had come up to Jerusalem, those who were of the circumcision contended with him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 11:3"}, "saying, \u201cYou went in to uncircumcised men, and ate with them!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 11:4"}, "But Peter began, and explained to them in order, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 11:5"}, "\u201cI was in the city of Joppa praying, and in a trance I saw a vision: a certain container descending, like it was a great\nsheet let down from heaven by four corners. It came as far as me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 11:6"}, "When I had looked intently at it, I considered, and saw the four-footed animals of the earth, wild animals, creeping\nthings, and birds of the sky. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 11:7"}, "I also heard a voice saying to me, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Rise, Peter, kill and eat!\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 11:8"}, "But I said, \u2018Not so, Lord, for nothing unholy or unclean has ever entered into my mouth.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 11:9"}, "But a voice answered me the second time out of heaven, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018What Allah has cleansed, don\u2019t you call\nunclean.\u2019"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 11:10"}, "This was done three times, and all were drawn up again into heaven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 11:11"}, "Behold, immediately three men stood before the house where I was, having been sent from Caesarea to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 11:12"}, "The Spirit told me to go with them, without discriminating. These six brothers also accompanied me, and we entered into\nthe man\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 11:13"}, "He told us how he had seen the angel standing in his house, and saying to him, \u2018Send to Joppa, and get Shima\u2019un, who is\ncalled Peter, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 11:14"}, "who will speak to you words by which you will be saved, you and all your house.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 11:15"}, "As I began to speak, the Holy Spirit fell on them, even as on us at the beginning.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 11:16"}, "I remembered the word of the Lord, how he said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Yahya indeed baptised in water, but you will be baptised in the Holy\nSpirit.\u2019"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 11:17"}, "If then Allah gave to them the same gift as us, when we believed in the Lord Al Masih Isa, who was I, that I could\nwithstand Allah?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 11:18"}, "When they heard these things, they held their peace, and glorified Allah, saying, \u201cThen Allah has also granted to the\nGentiles repentance to life!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 11:19"}, "They therefore who were scattered abroad by the oppression that arose about Stephen travelled as far as Phoenicia,\nCyprus, and Antioch, speaking the word to no one except to Jews only.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 11:20"}, "But there were some of them, men of Cyprus and Cyrene, who, when they had come to Antioch, spoke to the\nHellenists,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A Hellenist is someone who keeps Greek customs and\nculture."]}], "caller": "+"}, " preaching the Lord Isa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 11:21"}, "The hand of the Lord was with them, and a great number believed and turned to the Lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 11:22"}, "The report concerning them came to the ears of the assembly which was in Jerusalem. They sent out Barnabas to go as far\nas Antioch, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 11:23"}, "who, when he had come, and had seen the grace of Allah, was glad. He exhorted them all, that with purpose of heart they\nshould remain near to the Lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 11:24"}, "For he was a good man, and full of the Holy Spirit and of faith, and many people were added to the Lord.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 11:25"}, "Barnabas went out to Tarsus to look for Saul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 11:26"}, "When he had found him, he brought him to Antioch. For a whole year they were gathered together with the assembly, and\ntaught many people. The disciples were first called Christians in Antioch.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 11:27"}, "Now in these days, prophets came down from Jerusalem to Antioch.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 11:28"}, "One of them named Agabus stood up, and indicated by the Spirit that there should be a great famine all over the world,\nwhich also happened in the days of Claudius. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 11:29"}, "As any of the disciples had plenty, each determined to send relief to the brothers who lived in Judea;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 11:30"}, "which they also did, sending it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 12:1"}, "Now about that time, King Herod stretched out his hands to oppress some of the assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 12:2"}, "He killed Yaqub, the brother of Yuhanna, with the sword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 12:3"}, "When he saw that it pleased the Jews, he proceeded to seize Peter also. This was during the days of unleavened bread.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 12:4"}, "When he had arrested him, he put him in prison, and delivered him to four squads of four soldiers each to guard him,\nintending to bring him out to the people after the Passover. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 12:5"}, "Peter therefore was kept in the prison, but constant prayer was made by the assembly to Allah for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 12:6"}, "The same night when Herod was about to bring him out, Peter was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains.\nGuards in front of the door kept the prison. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 12:7"}, "And behold, an angel of the Lord stood by him, and a light shone in the cell. He struck Peter on the side, and woke him\nup, saying, \u201cStand up quickly!\u201d His chains fell off his hands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 12:8"}, "The angel said to him, \u201cGet dressed and put on your sandals.\u201d He did so. He said to him, \u201cPut on your cloak and follow\nme.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 12:9"}, "And he went out and followed him. He didn\u2019t know that what was being done by the angel was real, but thought he saw a\nvision. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 12:10"}, "When they were past the first and the second guard, they came to the iron gate that leads into the city, which opened to\nthem by itself. They went out, and went down one street, and immediately the angel departed from him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 12:11"}, "When Peter had come to himself, he said, \u201cNow I truly know that the Lord has sent out his angel and delivered me out of\nthe hand of Herod, and from everything the Jewish people were expecting.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 12:12"}, "Thinking about that, he came to the house of Maryam, the mother of Yuhanna who was called Marqus, where many were\ngathered together and were praying. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 12:13"}, "When Peter knocked at the door of the gate, a servant girl named Rhoda came to answer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 12:14"}, "When she recognised Peter\u2019s voice, she didn\u2019t open the gate for joy, but ran in, and reported that Peter was standing in\nfront of the gate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 12:15"}, "They said to her, \u201cYou are crazy!\u201d But she insisted that it was so. They said, \u201cIt is his angel.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 12:16"}, "But Peter continued knocking. When they had opened, they saw him, and were amazed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 12:17"}, "But he, beckoning to them with his hand to be silent, declared to them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. He\nsaid, \u201cTell these things to Yaqub and to the brothers.\u201d Then he departed and went to another place.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 12:18"}, "Now as soon as it was day, there was no small stir amongst the soldiers about what had become of Peter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 12:19"}, "When Herod had sought for him, and didn\u2019t find him, he examined the guards, then commanded that they should be put to\ndeath. He went down from Judea to Caesarea, and stayed there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 12:20"}, "Now Herod was very angry with the people of Tyre and Sidon. They came with one accord to him, and, having made Blastus,\nthe king\u2019s personal aide, their friend, they asked for peace, because their country depended on the king\u2019s country for food.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 12:21"}, "On an appointed day, Herod dressed himself in royal clothing, sat on the throne, and gave a speech to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 12:22"}, "The people shouted, \u201cThe voice of a god, and not of a man!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 12:23"}, "Immediately an angel of the Lord struck him, because he didn\u2019t give Allah the glory. Then he was eaten by worms and died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 12:24"}, "But the word of Allah grew and multiplied. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 12:25"}, "Barnabas and Saul returned to", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cfrom\u201d instead of\n\u201cto\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Jerusalem when they had fulfilled their service, also taking with them Yuhanna who was called Marqus.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 13:1"}, "Now in the assembly that was at Antioch there were some prophets and teachers: Barnabas, Simeon who was called Niger,\nLucius of Cyrene, Manaen the foster brother of Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 13:2"}, "As they served the Lord and fasted, the Holy Spirit said, \u201cSeparate Barnabas and Saul for me, for the work to which I have\ncalled them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 13:3"}, "Then, when they had fasted and prayed and laid their hands on them, they sent them away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 13:4"}, "So, being sent out by the Holy Spirit, they went down to Seleucia. From there they sailed to Cyprus.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 13:5"}, "When they were at Salamis, they proclaimed Allah\u2019s word in the Jewish synagogues. They also had Yuhanna as their\nattendant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 13:6"}, "When they had gone through the island to Paphos, they found a certain sorcerer, a false prophet, a Jew, whose name was Bar\nIsa, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 13:7"}, "who was with the proconsul, Sergius Paulus, a man of understanding. This man summoned Barnabas and Saul, and sought to\nhear the word of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 13:8"}, "But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn the proconsul away from the\nfaith. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 13:9"}, "But Saul, who is also called Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit, fastened his eyes on him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 13:10"}, "and said, \u201cYou son of the Iblis, full of all deceit and all cunning, you enemy of all righteousness, will you not cease\nto pervert the right ways of the Lord? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 13:11"}, "Now, behold, the hand of the Lord is on you, and you will be blind, not seeing the sun for a season!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Immediately a mist and darkness fell on him. He went around seeking someone to lead him by the hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 13:12"}, "Then the proconsul, when he saw what was done, believed, being astonished at the teaching of the Lord.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 13:13"}, "Now Paul and his company set sail from Paphos, and came to Perga in Pamphylia. Yuhanna departed from them and returned to\nJerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 13:14"}, "But they, passing on from Perga, came to Antioch of Pisidia. They went into the synagogue on the Sabbath day, and sat\ndown. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 13:15"}, "After the reading of the law and the prophets, the rulers of the synagogue sent to them, saying, \u201cBrothers, if you have\nany word of exhortation for the people, speak.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 13:16"}, "Paul stood up, and beckoning with his hand said, \u201cMen of Israel, and you who fear Allah, listen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 13:17"}, "The Allah of this people", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR, NU add \u201cIsrael\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " chose our fathers, and exalted the people when they\nstayed as aliens in the land of Egypt, and with an uplifted arm, he led them out of it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 13:18"}, "For a period of about forty years he put up with them in the wilderness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 13:19"}, "When he had destroyed seven nations in the land of Canaan, he gave them their land for an inheritance for about four\nhundred and fifty years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 13:20"}, "After these things, he gave them judges until Samuel the prophet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 13:21"}, "Afterward they asked for a king, and Allah gave to them Saul the son of Kish, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, for forty\nyears. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 13:22"}, "When he had removed him, he raised up Dawood to be their king, to whom he also testified, \u2018I have found Dawood the son of\nJesse, a man after my heart, who will do all my will.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 13:23"}, "From this man\u2019s offspring, Allah has brought salvation", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR, NU read \u201ca Saviour, Isa\u201d instead of \u201csalvation\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " to Israel according to his promise,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 13:24"}, "before his coming, when Yahya had first preached the baptism of repentance to\nIsrael.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR, NU read \u201cto all the people of Israel\u201d instead of \u201cto\nIsrael\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 13:25"}, "As Yahya was fulfilling his course, he said, \u2018What do you suppose that I am? I am not he. But behold, one comes after me,\nthe sandals of whose feet I am not worthy to untie.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 13:26"}, "Brothers, children of the stock of Ibrahim, and those amongst you who fear Allah, the word of this salvation is sent out\nto you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 13:27"}, "For those who dwell in Jerusalem, and their rulers, because they didn\u2019t know him, nor the voices of the prophets which\nare read every Sabbath, fulfilled them by condemning him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 13:28"}, "Though they found no cause for death, they still asked Pilate to have him killed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 13:29"}, "When they had fulfilled all things that were written about him, they took him down from the tree, and laid him in a tomb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 13:30"}, "But Allah raised him from the dead, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 13:31"}, "and he was seen for many days by those who came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are his witnesses to the\npeople. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 13:32"}, "We bring you good news of the promise made to the fathers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 13:33"}, "that Allah has fulfilled this to us, their children, in that he raised up Isa. As it is also written in the second psalm,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018You are my Son. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Today I have become your father.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 2:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 13:34"}, "\u201cConcerning that he raised him up from the dead, now no more to return to corruption, he has spoken thus: \u2018I will give\nyou the holy and sure blessings of Dawood.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n55:3"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 13:35"}, "Therefore he says also in another psalm, \u2018You will not allow your Holy One to see\ndecay.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:35 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 16:10"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 13:36"}, "For Dawood, after he had in his own generation served the counsel of Allah, fell asleep, was laid with his fathers, and\nsaw decay. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 13:37"}, "But he whom Allah raised up saw no decay. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 13:38"}, "Be it known to you therefore, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:38 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may\nalso be correctly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " that through this man is proclaimed to you remission of\nsins, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 13:39"}, "and by him everyone who believes is justified from all things, from which you could not be justified by the law of Musa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 13:40"}, "Beware therefore, lest that come on you which is spoken in the prophets:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 13:41"}, "\u2018Behold, you scoffers, and wonder, and perish; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for I work a work in your days, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a work which you will in no way believe, if one declares it to you.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:41 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Habakkuk 1:5"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 13:42"}, "So when the Jews went out of the synagogue, the Gentiles begged that these words might be preached to them the next\nSabbath. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "ACT 13:43"}, "Now when the synagogue broke up, many of the Jews and of the devout proselytes followed Paul and Barnabas; who, speaking\nto them, urged them to continue in the grace of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "ACT 13:44"}, "The next Sabbath, almost the whole city was gathered together to hear the word of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "ACT 13:45"}, "But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with jealousy, and contradicted the things which were spoken by\nPaul, and blasphemed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "ACT 13:46"}, "Paul and Barnabas spoke out boldly, and said, \u201cIt was necessary that Allah\u2019s word should be spoken to you first. Since\nindeed you thrust it from yourselves, and judge yourselves unworthy of eternal life, behold, we turn to the Gentiles.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "ACT 13:47"}, "For so has the Lord commanded us, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018I have set you as a light for the Gentiles, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you should bring salvation to the uttermost parts of the earth.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 49:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "ACT 13:48"}, "As the Gentiles heard this, they were glad, and glorified the word of Allah. As many as were appointed to eternal life\nbelieved. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "ACT 13:49"}, "The Lord\u2019s word was spread abroad throughout all the region.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "ACT 13:50"}, "But the Jews stirred up the devout and prominent women and the chief men of the city, and stirred up a persecution\nagainst Paul and Barnabas, and threw them out of their borders. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "ACT 13:51"}, "But they shook off the dust of their feet against them, and came to Iconium.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "ACT 13:52"}, "The disciples were filled with joy and with the Holy Spirit.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 14:1"}, "In Iconium, they entered together into the synagogue of the Jews, and so spoke that a great multitude both of Jews and of\nGreeks believed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 14:2"}, "But the disbelieving", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, disobedient"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Jews stirred up and embittered the souls of the Gentiles against\nthe brothers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 14:3"}, "Therefore they stayed there a long time, speaking boldly in the Lord, who testified to the word of his grace, granting\nsigns and wonders to be done by their hands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 14:4"}, "But the multitude of the city was divided. Part sided with the Jews, and part with the apostles.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 14:5"}, "When some of both the Gentiles and the Jews, with their rulers, made a violent attempt to mistreat and stone them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 14:6"}, "they became aware of it and fled to the cities of Lycaonia, Lystra, Derbe, and the surrounding region.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 14:7"}, "There they preached the Good News. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 14:8"}, "At Lystra a certain man sat, impotent in his feet, a cripple from his mother\u2019s womb, who never had walked.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 14:9"}, "He was listening to Paul speaking, who, fastening eyes on him, and seeing that he had faith to be made whole,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 14:10"}, "said with a loud voice, \u201cStand upright on your feet!\u201d He leapt up and walked.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 14:11"}, "When the multitude saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their voice, saying in the language of Lycaonia, \u201cThe gods have\ncome down to us in the likeness of men!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 14:12"}, "They called Barnabas \u201cJupiter\u201d, and Paul \u201cMercury\u201d, because he was the chief speaker.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 14:13"}, "The priest of Jupiter, whose temple was in front of their city, brought oxen and garlands to the gates, and would have\nmade a sacrifice along with the multitudes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 14:14"}, "But when the apostles, Barnabas and Paul, heard of it, they tore their clothes, and sprang into the multitude, crying\nout, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 14:15"}, "\u201cMen, why are you doing these things? We also are men of like passions with you, and bring you good news, that you should\nturn from these vain things to the living Allah, who made the sky, the earth, the sea, and all that is in them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 14:16"}, "who in the generations gone by allowed all the nations to walk in their own ways.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 14:17"}, "Yet he didn\u2019t leave himself without witness, in that he did good and gave\nyou", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cus\u201d instead of \u201cyou\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " rains from the sky and fruitful seasons, filling our hearts with food\nand gladness.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 14:18"}, "Even saying these things, they hardly stopped the multitudes from making a sacrifice to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 14:19"}, "But some Jews from Antioch and Iconium came there, and having persuaded the multitudes, they stoned Paul, and dragged him\nout of the city, supposing that he was dead. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 14:20"}, "But as the disciples stood around him, he rose up, and entered into the city. On the next day he went out with Barnabas\nto Derbe. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 14:21"}, "When they had preached the Good News to that city, and had made many disciples, they returned to Lystra, Iconium, and\nAntioch, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 14:22"}, "strengthening the souls of the disciples, exhorting them to continue in the faith, and that through many afflictions we\nmust enter into Allah\u2019s Kingdom. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 14:23"}, "When they had appointed elders for them in every assembly, and had prayed with fasting, they commended them to the Lord,\non whom they had believed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 14:24"}, "They passed through Pisidia, and came to Pamphylia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 14:25"}, "When they had spoken the word in Perga, they went down to Attalia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 14:26"}, "From there they sailed to Antioch, from where they had been committed to the grace of Allah for the work which they had\nfulfilled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 14:27"}, "When they had arrived, and had gathered the assembly together, they reported all the things that Allah had done with\nthem, and that he had opened a door of faith to the nations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 14:28"}, "They stayed there with the disciples for a long time. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 15:1"}, "Some men came down from Judea and taught the brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may also be correctly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d\nor \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \u201cUnless you are circumcised after the custom of Musa, you can\u2019t be saved.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 15:2"}, "Therefore when Paul and Barnabas had no small discord and discussion with them, they appointed Paul and Barnabas, and some\nothers of them, to go up to Jerusalem to the apostles and elders about this question.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 15:3"}, "They, being sent on their way by the assembly, passed through both Phoenicia and Samaria, declaring the conversion of the\nGentiles. They caused great joy to all the brothers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 15:4"}, "When they had come to Jerusalem, they were received by the assembly and the apostles and the elders, and they reported\neverything that Allah had done with them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 15:5"}, "But some of the sect of the Pharisees who believed rose up, saying, \u201cIt is necessary to circumcise them, and to command\nthem to keep the law of Musa.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 15:6"}, "The apostles and the elders were gathered together to see about this matter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 15:7"}, "When there had been much discussion, Peter rose up and said to them, \u201cBrothers, you know that a good while ago Allah made\na choice amongst you that by my mouth the nations should hear the word of the Good News and believe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 15:8"}, "Allah, who knows the heart, testified about them, giving them the Holy Spirit, just like he did to us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 15:9"}, "He made no distinction between us and them, cleansing their hearts by faith.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 15:10"}, "Now therefore why do you tempt Allah, that you should put a yoke on the neck of the disciples which neither our fathers\nnor we were able to bear? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 15:11"}, "But we believe that we are saved through the grace of the Lord Isa,\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cMasih\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " just as they are.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 15:12"}, "All the multitude kept silence, and they listened to Barnabas and Paul reporting what signs and wonders Allah had done\namongst the nations through them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 15:13"}, "After they were silent, Yaqub answered, \u201cBrothers, listen to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 15:14"}, "Simeon has reported how Allah first visited the nations to take out of them a people for his name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 15:15"}, "This agrees with the words of the prophets. As it is written,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 15:16"}, "\u2018After these things I will return. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will again build the tabernacle of Dawood, which has fallen.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will again build its ruins. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will set it up \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 15:17"}, "that the rest of men may seek after the Lord; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["all the Gentiles who are called by my name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["says the Lord, who does all these things.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Amos\n9:11-12"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 15:18"}, "\u201cAll of Allah\u2019s works are known to him from eternity. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 15:19"}, "Therefore my judgement is that we don\u2019t trouble those from amongst the Gentiles who turn to Allah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 15:20"}, "but that we write to them that they abstain from the pollution of idols, from sexual immorality, from what is strangled,\nand from blood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 15:21"}, "For Musa from generations of old has in every city those who preach him, being read in the synagogues every Sabbath.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 15:22"}, "Then it seemed good to the apostles and the elders, with the whole assembly, to choose men out of their company, and send\nthem to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas: Yehuda called Barsabbas, and Silas, chief men amongst the brothers.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may also be correctly translated \u201cbrothers and\nsisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 15:23"}, "They wrote these things by their hand: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cThe apostles, the elders, and the brothers, to the brothers who are of the Gentiles in Antioch, Syria, and Cilicia:\ngreetings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 15:24"}, "Because we have heard that some who went out from us have troubled you with words, unsettling your souls, saying, \u2018You\nmust be circumcised and keep the law,\u2019 to whom we gave no commandment;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 15:25"}, "it seemed good to us, having come to one accord, to choose out men and send them to you with our beloved Barnabas and\nPaul, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 15:26"}, "men who have risked their lives for the name of our Lord Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 15:27"}, "We have sent therefore Yehuda and Silas, who themselves will also tell you the same things by word of mouth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 15:28"}, "For it seemed good to the Holy Spirit, and to us, to lay no greater burden on you than these necessary things:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 15:29"}, "that you abstain from things sacrificed to idols, from blood, from things strangled, and from sexual immorality, from\nwhich if you keep yourselves, it will be well with you. Farewell.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 15:30"}, "So, when they were sent off, they came to Antioch. Having gathered the multitude together, they delivered the letter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 15:31"}, "When they had read it, they rejoiced over the encouragement.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 15:32"}, "Yehuda and Silas, also being prophets themselves, encouraged the brothers with many words and strengthened them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 15:33"}, "After they had spent some time there, they were sent back with greetings from the brothers to the apostles.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 15:34"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Some manuscripts add: "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "fqa", "content": ["But it seemed good to Silas to stay there.\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 15:35"}, "But Paul and Barnabas stayed in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of the Lord, with many others also.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 15:36"}, "After some days Paul said to Barnabas, \u201cLet\u2019s return now and visit our brothers in every city in which we proclaimed the\nword of the Lord, to see how they are doing.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 15:37"}, "Barnabas planned to take Yuhanna, who was called Marqus, with them also.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 15:38"}, "But Paul didn\u2019t think that it was a good idea to take with them someone who had withdrawn from them in Pamphylia, and\ndidn\u2019t go with them to do the work. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 15:39"}, "Then the contention grew so sharp that they separated from each other. Barnabas took Marqus with him and sailed away to\nCyprus, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 15:40"}, "but Paul chose Silas and went out, being commended by the brothers to the grace of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 15:41"}, "He went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the assemblies.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 16:1"}, "He came to Derbe and Lystra: and behold, a certain disciple was there, named Timothy, the son of a Jewess who believed;\nbut his father was a Greek. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 16:2"}, "The brothers who were at Lystra and Iconium gave a good testimony about him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 16:3"}, "Paul wanted to have him go out with him, and he took and circumcised him because of the Jews who were in those parts; for\nthey all knew that his father was a Greek. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 16:4"}, "As they went on their way through the cities, they delivered the decrees to them to keep which had been ordained by the\napostles and elders who were at Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 16:5"}, "So the assemblies were strengthened in the faith, and increased in number daily.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 16:6"}, "When they had gone through the region of Phrygia and Galatia, they were forbidden by the Holy Spirit to speak the word in\nAsia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 16:7"}, "When they had come opposite Mysia, they tried to go into Bithynia, but the Spirit didn\u2019t allow them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 16:8"}, "Passing by Mysia, they came down to Troas. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 16:9"}, "A vision appeared to Paul in the night. There was a man of Macedonia standing, begging him, and saying, \u201cCome over into\nMacedonia and help us.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 16:10"}, "When he had seen the vision, immediately we sought to go out to Macedonia, concluding that the Lord had called us to\npreach the Good News to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 16:11"}, "Setting sail therefore from Troas, we made a straight course to Samothrace, and the day following to Neapolis;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 16:12"}, "and from there to Philippi, which is a city of Macedonia, the foremost of the district, a Roman colony. We were staying\nsome days in this city. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 16:13"}, "On the Sabbath day we went outside of the city by a riverside, where we supposed there was a place of prayer, and we sat\ndown and spoke to the women who had come together. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 16:14"}, "A certain woman named Lydia, a seller of purple, of the city of Thyatira, one who worshipped Allah, heard us. The Lord\nopened her heart to listen to the things which were spoken by Paul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 16:15"}, "When she and her household were baptised, she begged us, saying, \u201cIf you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come\ninto my house and stay.\u201d So she persuaded us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 16:16"}, "As we were going to prayer, a certain girl having a spirit of divination met us, who brought her masters much gain by\nfortune telling. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 16:17"}, "Following Paul and us, she cried out, \u201cThese men are servants of the Most High Allah, who proclaim to us a way of\nsalvation!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 16:18"}, "She was doing this for many days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But Paul, becoming greatly annoyed, turned and said to the spirit, \u201cI command you in the name of Al Masih Isa to come out of\nher!\u201d It came out that very hour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 16:19"}, "But when her masters saw that the hope of their gain was gone, they seized Paul and Silas, and dragged them into the\nmarketplace before the rulers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 16:20"}, "When they had brought them to the magistrates, they said, \u201cThese men, being Jews, are agitating our city\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 16:21"}, "and advocate customs which it is not lawful for us to accept or to observe, being Romans.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 16:22"}, "The multitude rose up together against them and the magistrates tore their clothes from them, then commanded them to be\nbeaten with rods. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 16:23"}, "When they had laid many stripes on them, they threw them into prison, charging the jailer to keep them safely,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 16:24"}, "who, having received such a command, threw them into the inner prison, and secured their feet in the stocks.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 16:25"}, "But about midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to Allah, and the prisoners were listening to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 16:26"}, "Suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of the prison were shaken; and immediately all the doors\nwere opened, and everyone\u2019s bonds were loosened. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 16:27"}, "The jailer, being roused out of sleep and seeing the prison doors open, drew his sword and was about to kill himself,\nsupposing that the prisoners had escaped. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 16:28"}, "But Paul cried with a loud voice, saying, \u201cDon\u2019t harm yourself, for we are all here!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 16:29"}, "He called for lights, sprang in, fell down trembling before Paul and Silas,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 16:30"}, "brought them out, and said, \u201cSirs, what must I do to be saved?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 16:31"}, "They said, \u201cBelieve in the Lord Al Masih Isa, and you will be saved, you and your household.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 16:32"}, "They spoke the word of the Lord to him, and to all who were in his house.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 16:33"}, "He took them the same hour of the night and washed their stripes, and was immediately baptised, he and all his household.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 16:34"}, "He brought them up into his house, and set food before them, and rejoiced greatly, with all his household, having\nbelieved in Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 16:35"}, "But when it was day, the magistrates sent the sergeants, saying, \u201cLet those men go.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 16:36"}, "The jailer reported these words to Paul, saying, \u201cThe magistrates have sent to let you go; now therefore come out and go\nin peace.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 16:37"}, "But Paul said to them, \u201cThey have beaten us publicly without a trial, men who are Romans, and have cast us into prison!\nDo they now release us secretly? No, most certainly, but let them come themselves and bring us out!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 16:38"}, "The sergeants reported these words to the magistrates, and they were afraid when they heard that they were Romans,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 16:39"}, "and they came and begged them. When they had brought them out, they asked them to depart from the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 16:40"}, "They went out of the prison, and entered into Lydia\u2019s house. When they had seen the brothers, they encouraged them, then\ndeparted. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 17:1"}, "Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica, where there was a Jewish synagogue.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 17:2"}, "Paul, as was his custom, went in to them, and for three Sabbath days reasoned with them from the Scriptures,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 17:3"}, "explaining and demonstrating that the Masih had to suffer and rise again from the dead, and saying, \u201cThis Isa, whom I\nproclaim to you, is the Masih.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 17:4"}, "Some of them were persuaded and joined Paul and Silas, of the devout Greeks a great multitude, and not a few of the chief\nwomen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 17:5"}, "But the unpersuaded Jews took along", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cAnd the Jews who were unpersuaded, becoming envious and\ntaking along\u201d instead of \u201cBut the unpersuaded Jews took along\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " some wicked men from the marketplace, and gathering a crowd,\nset the city in an uproar. Assaulting the house of Jason, they sought to bring them out to the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 17:6"}, "When they didn\u2019t find them, they dragged Jason and certain brothers\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may be also correctly translated \u201cbrothers and\nsisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " before the rulers of the city, crying, \u201cThese who have turned the world upside down have come here\nalso, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 17:7"}, "whom Jason has received. These all act contrary to the decrees of Caesar, saying that there is another king, Isa!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 17:8"}, "The multitude and the rulers of the city were troubled when they heard these things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 17:9"}, "When they had taken security from Jason and the rest, they let them go.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 17:10"}, "The brothers immediately sent Paul and Silas away by night to Beroea. When they arrived, they went into the Jewish\nsynagogue. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 17:11"}, "Now these were more noble than those in Thessalonica, in that they received the word with all readiness of mind,\nexamining the Scriptures daily to see whether these things were so.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 17:12"}, "Many of them therefore believed; also of the prominent Greek women, and not a few men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 17:13"}, "But when the Jews of Thessalonica had knowledge that the word of Allah was proclaimed by Paul at Beroea also, they came\nthere likewise, agitating the multitudes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 17:14"}, "Then the brothers immediately sent out Paul to go as far as to the sea, and Silas and Timothy still stayed there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 17:15"}, "But those who escorted Paul brought him as far as Athens. Receiving a commandment to Silas and Timothy that they should\ncome to him very quickly, they departed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 17:16"}, "Now while Paul waited for them at Athens, his spirit was provoked within him as he saw the city full of idols.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 17:17"}, "So he reasoned in the synagogue with the Jews and the devout persons, and in the marketplace every day with those who met\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 17:18"}, "Some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers also", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:18\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR omits \u201calso\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " were conversing with him. Some said, \u201cWhat does this babbler want to say?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Others said, \u201cHe seems to be advocating foreign deities,\u201d because he preached Isa and the resurrection.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 17:19"}, "They took hold of him and brought him to the Areopagus, saying, \u201cMay we know what this new teaching is, which you are\nspeaking about? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 17:20"}, "For you bring certain strange things to our ears. We want to know therefore what these things mean.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 17:21"}, "Now all the Athenians and the strangers living there spent their time in nothing else, but either to tell or to hear some\nnew thing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 17:22"}, "Paul stood in the middle of the Areopagus, and said, \u201cYou men of Athens, I perceive that you are very religious in all\nthings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 17:23"}, "For as I passed along and observed the objects of your worship, I also found an altar with this inscription: \u2018TO AN\nUNKNOWN ALLAH.\u2019 What therefore you worship in ignorance, I announce to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 17:24"}, "The Allah who made the world and all things in it, he, being Lord of heaven and earth, doesn\u2019t dwell in temples made with\nhands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 17:25"}, "He isn\u2019t served by men\u2019s hands, as though he needed anything, seeing he himself gives to all life and breath, and all\nthings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 17:26"}, "He made from one blood every nation of men to dwell on all the surface of the earth, having determined appointed seasons,\nand the boundaries of their dwellings, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 17:27"}, "that they should seek the Lord, if perhaps they might reach out for him and find him, though he is not far from each one\nof us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 17:28"}, "\u2018For in him we live, move, and have our being.\u2019 As some of your own poets have said, \u2018For we are also his offspring.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 17:29"}, "Being then the offspring of Allah, we ought not to think that the Divine Nature is like gold, or silver, or stone,\nengraved by art and design of man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 17:30"}, "The times of ignorance therefore Allah overlooked. But now he commands that all people everywhere should repent,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 17:31"}, "because he has appointed a day in which he will judge the world in righteousness by the man whom he has ordained; of\nwhich he has given assurance to all men, in that he has raised him from the dead.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 17:32"}, "Now when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked; but others said, \u201cWe want to hear you again concerning\nthis.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 17:33"}, "Thus Paul went out from amongst them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 17:34"}, "But certain men joined with him and believed, amongst whom also was Dionysius the Areopagite, and a woman named Damaris,\nand others with them. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 18:1"}, "After these things Paul departed from Athens, and came to Corinth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 18:2"}, "He found a certain Jew named Aquila, a man of Pontus by race, who had recently come from Italy, with his wife Priscilla,\nbecause Claudius had commanded all the Jews to depart from Rome. He came to them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 18:3"}, "and because he practised the same trade, he lived with them and worked, for by trade they were tent makers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 18:4"}, "He reasoned in the synagogue every Sabbath and persuaded Jews and Greeks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 18:5"}, "But when Silas and Timothy came down from Macedonia, Paul was compelled by the Spirit, testifying to the Jews that Isa was\nthe Masih. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 18:6"}, "When they opposed him and blasphemed, he shook out his clothing and said to them, \u201cYour blood be on your own heads! I am\nclean. From now on, I will go to the Gentiles!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 18:7"}, "He departed there, and went into the house of a certain man named Justus, one who worshipped Allah, whose house was next\ndoor to the synagogue. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 18:8"}, "Crispus, the ruler of the synagogue, believed in the Lord with all his house. Many of the Corinthians, when they heard,\nbelieved and were baptised. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 18:9"}, "The Lord said to Paul in the night by a vision, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, but speak and don\u2019t be silent;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 18:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for I am with you, and no one will attack you to harm you, for I have many people in this\ncity.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 18:11"}, "He lived there a year and six months, teaching the word of Allah amongst them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 18:12"}, "But when Gallio was proconsul of Achaia, the Jews with one accord rose up against Paul and brought him before the\njudgement seat, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 18:13"}, "saying, \u201cThis man persuades men to worship Allah contrary to the law.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 18:14"}, "But when Paul was about to open his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews, \u201cIf indeed it were a matter of wrong or of wicked\ncrime, you Jews, it would be reasonable that I should bear with you;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 18:15"}, "but if they are questions about words and names and your own law, look to it yourselves. For I don\u2019t want to be a judge\nof these matters.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 18:16"}, "So he drove them from the judgement seat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 18:17"}, "Then all the Greeks seized Sosthenes, the ruler of the synagogue, and beat him before the judgement seat. Gallio didn\u2019t\ncare about any of these things. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 18:18"}, "Paul, having stayed after this many more days, took his leave of the brothers,\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may also be correctly translated \u201cbrothers and\nsisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and sailed from there for Syria, together with Priscilla and Aquila. He shaved his head in\nCenchreae, for he had a vow. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 18:19"}, "He came to Ephesus, and he left them there; but he himself entered into the synagogue, and reasoned with the Jews.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 18:20"}, "When they asked him to stay with them a longer time, he declined;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 18:21"}, "but taking his leave of them, he said, \u201cI must by all means keep this coming feast in Jerusalem, but I will return again\nto you if Allah wills.\u201d Then he set sail from Ephesus. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 18:22"}, "When he had landed at Caesarea, he went up and greeted the assembly, and went down to Antioch.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 18:23"}, "Having spent some time there, he departed, and went through the region of Galatia, and Phrygia, in order, establishing\nall the disciples. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 18:24"}, "Now a certain Jew named Apollos, an Alexandrian by race, an eloquent man, came to Ephesus. He was mighty in the\nScriptures. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 18:25"}, "This man had been instructed in the way of the Lord; and being fervent in spirit, he spoke and taught accurately the\nthings concerning Isa, although he knew only the baptism of Yahya.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 18:26"}, "He began to speak boldly in the synagogue. But when Priscilla and Aquila heard him, they took him aside, and explained to\nhim the way of Allah more accurately. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 18:27"}, "When he had determined to pass over into Achaia, the brothers encouraged him, and wrote to the disciples to receive him.\nWhen he had come, he greatly helped those who had believed through grace;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 18:28"}, "for he powerfully refuted the Jews, publicly showing by the Scriptures that Isa was the Masih.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 19:1"}, "While Apollos was at Corinth, Paul, having passed through the upper country, came to Ephesus and found certain disciples.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 19:2"}, "He said to them, \u201cDid you receive the Holy Spirit when you believed?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to him, \u201cNo, we haven\u2019t even heard that there is a Holy Spirit.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 19:3"}, "He said, \u201cInto what then were you baptised?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cInto Yahya\u2019s baptism.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 19:4"}, "Paul said, \u201cYahya indeed baptised with the baptism of repentance, saying to the people that they should believe in the one\nwho would come after him, that is, in Isa.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 19:5"}, "When they heard this, they were baptised in the name of the Lord Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 19:6"}, "When Paul had laid his hands on them, the Holy Spirit came on them and they spoke with other languages and prophesied.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 19:7"}, "They were about twelve men in all. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 19:8"}, "He entered into the synagogue and spoke boldly for a period of three months, reasoning and persuading about the things\nconcerning Allah\u2019s Kingdom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 19:9"}, "But when some were hardened and disobedient, speaking evil of the Way before the multitude, he departed from them, and\nseparated the disciples, reasoning daily in the school of Tyrannus.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 19:10"}, "This continued for two years, so that all those who lived in Asia heard the word of the Lord Isa, both Jews and Greeks.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 19:11"}, "Allah worked special miracles by the hands of Paul, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 19:12"}, "so that even handkerchiefs or aprons were carried away from his body to the sick, and the diseases departed from them,\nand the evil spirits went out. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 19:13"}, "But some of the itinerant Jews, exorcists, took on themselves to invoke over those who had the evil spirits the name of\nthe Lord Isa, saying, \u201cWe adjure you by Isa whom Paul preaches.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 19:14"}, "There were seven sons of one Sceva, a Jewish chief priest, who did this.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 19:15"}, "The evil spirit answered, \u201cIsa I know, and Paul I know, but who are you?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 19:16"}, "The man in whom the evil spirit was leapt on them, overpowered them, and prevailed against them, so that they fled out of\nthat house naked and wounded. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 19:17"}, "This became known to all, both Jews and Greeks, who lived at Ephesus. Fear fell on them all, and the name of the Lord Isa\nwas magnified. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 19:18"}, "Many also of those who had believed came, confessing, and declaring their deeds.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 19:19"}, "Many of those who practised magical arts brought their books together and burnt them in the sight of all. They counted\ntheir price, and found it to be fifty thousand pieces of silver.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["19:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The 50,000 pieces of silver here probably referred to 50,000 drachmas. If so, the value of the burnt books was\nequivalent to about 160 man-years of wages for agricultural labourers"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 19:20"}, "So the word of the Lord was growing and becoming mighty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 19:21"}, "Now after these things had ended, Paul determined in the Spirit, when he had passed through Macedonia and Achaia, to go\nto Jerusalem, saying, \u201cAfter I have been there, I must also see Rome.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 19:22"}, "Having sent into Macedonia two of those who served him, Timothy and Erastus, he himself stayed in Asia for a while.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 19:23"}, "About that time there arose no small disturbance concerning the Way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 19:24"}, "For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith who made silver shrines of Artemis, brought no little business to the\ncraftsmen, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 19:25"}, "whom he gathered together, with the workmen of like occupation, and said, \u201cSirs, you know that by this business we have\nour wealth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 19:26"}, "You see and hear that not at Ephesus alone, but almost throughout all Asia, this Paul has persuaded and turned away many\npeople, saying that they are no gods that are made with hands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 19:27"}, "Not only is there danger that this our trade come into disrepute, but also that the temple of the great goddess Artemis\nwill be counted as nothing and her majesty destroyed, whom all Asia and the world worships.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 19:28"}, "When they heard this they were filled with anger, and cried out, saying, \u201cGreat is Artemis of the Ephesians!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 19:29"}, "The whole city was filled with confusion, and they rushed with one accord into the theatre, having seized Gaius and\nAristarchus, men of Macedonia, Paul\u2019s companions in travel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 19:30"}, "When Paul wanted to enter in to the people, the disciples didn\u2019t allow him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 19:31"}, "Certain also of the Asiarchs, being his friends, sent to him and begged him not to venture into the theatre.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 19:32"}, "Some therefore cried one thing, and some another, for the assembly was in confusion. Most of them didn\u2019t know why they\nhad come together. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 19:33"}, "They brought Alexander out of the multitude, the Jews putting him forward. Alexander beckoned with his hand, and would\nhave made a defence to the people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 19:34"}, "But when they perceived that he was a Jew, all with one voice for a time of about two hours cried out, \u201cGreat is Artemis\nof the Ephesians!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 19:35"}, "When the town clerk had quieted the multitude, he said, \u201cYou men of Ephesus, what man is there who doesn\u2019t know that the\ncity of the Ephesians is temple keeper of the great goddess Artemis, and of the image which fell down from Zeus?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 19:36"}, "Seeing then that these things can\u2019t be denied, you ought to be quiet and to do nothing rash.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 19:37"}, "For you have brought these men here, who are neither robbers of temples nor blasphemers of your goddess.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 19:38"}, "If therefore Demetrius and the craftsmen who are with him have a matter against anyone, the courts are open, and there\nare proconsuls. Let them press charges against one another. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 19:39"}, "But if you seek anything about other matters, it will be settled in the regular assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 19:40"}, "For indeed we are in danger of being accused concerning today\u2019s riot, there being no cause. Concerning it, we wouldn\u2019t be\nable to give an account of this commotion.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 19:41"}, "When he had thus spoken, he dismissed the assembly. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 20:1"}, "After the uproar had ceased, Paul sent for the disciples, took leave of them, and departed to go into Macedonia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 20:2"}, "When he had gone through those parts, and had encouraged them with many words, he came into Greece.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 20:3"}, "When he had spent three months there, and a plot was made against him by Jews as he was about to set sail for Syria, he\ndetermined to return through Macedonia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 20:4"}, "These accompanied him as far as Asia: Sopater of Beroea; Aristarchus and Secundus of the Thessalonians; Gaius of Derbe;\nTimothy; and Tychicus and Trophimus of Asia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 20:5"}, "But these had gone ahead, and were waiting for us at Troas.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 20:6"}, "We sailed away from Philippi after the days of Unleavened Bread, and came to them at Troas in five days, where we stayed\nseven days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 20:7"}, "On the first day of the week, when the disciples were gathered together to break bread, Paul talked with them, intending\nto depart on the next day, and continued his speech until midnight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 20:8"}, "There were many lights in the upper room where we", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:8\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cthey\u201d instead of \u201cwe\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " were gathered together. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 20:9"}, "A certain young man named Eutychus sat in the window, weighed down with deep sleep. As Paul spoke still longer, being\nweighed down by his sleep, he fell down from the third floor and was taken up dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 20:10"}, "Paul went down and fell upon him, and embracing him said, \u201cDon\u2019t be troubled, for his life is in him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 20:11"}, "When he had gone up, and had broken bread and eaten, and had talked with them a long while, even until break of day, he\ndeparted. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 20:12"}, "They brought the boy in alive, and were greatly comforted.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 20:13"}, "But we, going ahead to the ship, set sail for Assos, intending to take Paul aboard there; for he had so arranged,\nintending himself to go by land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 20:14"}, "When he met us at Assos, we took him aboard, and came to Mitylene.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 20:15"}, "Sailing from there, we came the following day opposite Chios. The next day we touched at Samos and stayed at Trogyllium,\nand the day after we came to Miletus. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 20:16"}, "For Paul had determined to sail past Ephesus, that he might not have to spend time in Asia; for he was hastening, if it\nwere possible for him, to be in Jerusalem on the day of Pentecost.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 20:17"}, "From Miletus he sent to Ephesus, and called to himself the elders of the assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 20:18"}, "When they had come to him, he said to them, \u201cYou yourselves know, from the first day that I set foot in Asia, how I was\nwith you all the time, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 20:19"}, "serving the Lord with all humility, with many tears, and with trials which happened to me by the plots of the Jews;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 20:20"}, "how I didn\u2019t shrink from declaring to you anything that was profitable, teaching you publicly and from house to house,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 20:21"}, "testifying both to Jews and to Greeks repentance towards Allah, and faith towards our Lord\nIsa.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cMasih\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 20:22"}, "Now, behold, I go bound by the Spirit to Jerusalem, not knowing what will happen to me there;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 20:23"}, "except that the Holy Spirit testifies in every city, saying that bonds and afflictions wait for me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 20:24"}, "But these things don\u2019t count; nor do I hold my life dear to myself, so that I may finish my race with joy, and the\nministry which I received from the Lord Isa, to fully testify to the Good News of the grace of Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 20:25"}, "\u201cNow, behold, I know that you all, amongst whom I went about preaching Allah\u2019s Kingdom, will see my face no more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 20:26"}, "Therefore I testify to you today that I am clean from the blood of all men,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 20:27"}, "for I didn\u2019t shrink from declaring to you the whole counsel of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 20:28"}, "Take heed, therefore, to yourselves, and to all the flock, in which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to shepherd\nthe assembly of the Lord and ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR, NU omit \u201cthe Lord\nand\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Allah which he purchased with his own blood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 20:29"}, "For I know that after my departure, vicious wolves will enter in amongst you, not sparing the flock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 20:30"}, "Men will arise from amongst your own selves, speaking perverse things, to draw away the disciples after them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 20:31"}, "Therefore watch, remembering that for a period of three years I didn\u2019t cease to admonish everyone night and day with\ntears. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 20:32"}, "Now, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where the context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " I entrust you to Allah and to the word of his grace, which is able to\nbuild up, and to give you the inheritance amongst all those who are sanctified.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 20:33"}, "I coveted no one\u2019s silver, gold, or clothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 20:34"}, "You yourselves know that these hands served my necessities, and those who were with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 20:35"}, "In all things I gave you an example, that so labouring you ought to help the weak, and to remember the words of the Lord\nIsa, that he himself said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018It is more blessed to give than to\nreceive.\u2019"]}, "\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 20:36"}, "When he had spoken these things, he knelt down and prayed with them all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 20:37"}, "They all wept freely, and fell on Paul\u2019s neck and kissed him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 20:38"}, "sorrowing most of all because of the word which he had spoken, that they should see his face no more. Then they\naccompanied him to the ship. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 21:1"}, "When we had departed from them and had set sail, we came with a straight course to Cos, and the next day to Rhodes, and\nfrom there to Patara. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 21:2"}, "Having found a ship crossing over to Phoenicia, we went aboard, and set sail.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 21:3"}, "When we had come in sight of Cyprus, leaving it on the left hand, we sailed to Syria and landed at Tyre, for the ship was\nthere to unload her cargo. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 21:4"}, "Having found disciples, we stayed there seven days. These said to Paul through the Spirit that he should not go up to\nJerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 21:5"}, "When those days were over, we departed and went on our journey. They all, with wives and children, brought us on our way\nuntil we were out of the city. Kneeling down on the beach, we prayed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 21:6"}, "After saying goodbye to each other, we went on board the ship, and they returned home again.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 21:7"}, "When we had finished the voyage from Tyre, we arrived at Ptolemais. We greeted the brothers and stayed with them one day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 21:8"}, "On the next day, we who were Paul\u2019s companions departed, and came to Caesarea.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["We entered into the house of Philip the evangelist, who was one of the seven, and stayed with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 21:9"}, "Now this man had four virgin daughters who prophesied. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 21:10"}, "As we stayed there some days, a certain prophet named Agabus came down from Judea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 21:11"}, "Coming to us and taking Paul\u2019s belt, he bound his own feet and hands, and said, \u201cThe Holy Spirit says: \u2018So the Jews at\nJerusalem will bind the man who owns this belt, and will deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 21:12"}, "When we heard these things, both we and the people of that place begged him not to go up to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 21:13"}, "Then Paul answered, \u201cWhat are you doing, weeping and breaking my heart? For I am ready not only to be bound, but also to\ndie at Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Isa.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 21:14"}, "When he would not be persuaded, we ceased, saying, \u201cThe Lord\u2019s will be done.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 21:15"}, "After these days we took up our baggage and went up to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 21:16"}, "Some of the disciples from Caesarea also went with us, bringing one Mnason of Cyprus, an early disciple, with whom we\nwould stay. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 21:17"}, "When we had come to Jerusalem, the brothers received us gladly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 21:18"}, "The day following, Paul went in with us to Yaqub; and all the elders were present.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 21:19"}, "When he had greeted them, he reported one by one the things which Allah had worked amongst the Gentiles through his\nministry. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 21:20"}, "They, when they heard it, glorified Allah. They said to him, \u201cYou see, brother, how many thousands there are amongst the\nJews of those who have believed, and they are all zealous for the law.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 21:21"}, "They have been informed about you, that you teach all the Jews who are amongst the Gentiles to forsake Musa, telling them\nnot to circumcise their children and not to walk after the customs.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 21:22"}, "What then? The assembly must certainly meet, for they will hear that you have come.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 21:23"}, "Therefore do what we tell you. We have four men who have taken a vow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 21:24"}, "Take them and purify yourself with them, and pay their expenses for them, that they may shave their heads. Then all will\nknow that there is no truth in the things that they have been informed about you, but that you yourself also walk keeping the\nlaw. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 21:25"}, "But concerning the Gentiles who believe, we have written our decision that they should observe no such thing, except that\nthey should keep themselves from food offered to idols, from blood, from strangled things, and from sexual immorality.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 21:26"}, "Then Paul took the men, and the next day purified himself and went with them into the temple, declaring the fulfilment of\nthe days of purification, until the offering was offered for every one of them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 21:27"}, "When the seven days were almost completed, the Jews from Asia, when they saw him in the temple, stirred up all the\nmultitude and laid hands on him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 21:28"}, "crying out, \u201cMen of Israel, help! This is the man who teaches all men everywhere against the people, and the law, and\nthis place. Moreover, he also brought Greeks into the temple, and has defiled this holy place!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 21:29"}, "For they had seen Trophimus, the Ephesian, with him in the city, and they supposed that Paul had brought him into the\ntemple. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 21:30"}, "All the city was moved and the people ran together. They seized Paul and dragged him out of the temple. Immediately the\ndoors were shut. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 21:31"}, "As they were trying to kill him, news came up to the commanding officer of the regiment that all Jerusalem was in an\nuproar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 21:32"}, "Immediately he took soldiers and centurions and ran down to them. They, when they saw the chief captain and the soldiers,\nstopped beating Paul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 21:33"}, "Then the commanding officer came near, arrested him, commanded him to be bound with two chains, and enquired who he was\nand what he had done. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 21:34"}, "Some shouted one thing, and some another, amongst the crowd. When he couldn\u2019t find out the truth because of the noise, he\ncommanded him to be brought into the barracks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 21:35"}, "When he came to the stairs, he was carried by the soldiers because of the violence of the crowd;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 21:36"}, "for the multitude of the people followed after, crying out, \u201cAway with him!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 21:37"}, "As Paul was about to be brought into the barracks, he asked the commanding officer, \u201cMay I speak to you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cDo you know Greek? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 21:38"}, "Aren\u2019t you then the Egyptian, who before these days stirred up to sedition and led out into the wilderness the four\nthousand men of the Assassins?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 21:39"}, "But Paul said, \u201cI am a Jew, from Tarsus in Cilicia, a citizen of no insignificant city. I beg you, allow me to speak to\nthe people.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 21:40"}, "When he had given him permission, Paul, standing on the stairs, beckoned with his hand to the people. When there was a\ngreat silence, he spoke to them in the Hebrew language, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 22:1"}, "\u201cBrothers and fathers, listen to the defence which I now make to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 22:2"}, "When they heard that he spoke to them in the Hebrew language, they were even more quiet. He said,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 22:3"}, "\u201cI am indeed a Jew, born in Tarsus of Cilicia, but brought up in this city at the feet of Gamaliel, instructed according\nto the strict tradition of the law of our fathers, being zealous for Allah, even as you all are today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 22:4"}, "I persecuted this Way to the death, binding and delivering into prisons both men and women.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 22:5"}, "As also the high priest and all the council of the elders testify, from whom also I received letters to the brothers, and\ntravelled to Damascus to bring them also who were there to Jerusalem in bonds to be punished.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 22:6"}, "As I made my journey, and came close to Damascus, about noon, suddenly a great light shone around me from the sky.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 22:7"}, "I fell to the ground, and heard a voice saying to me, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting\nme?\u2019"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 22:8"}, "I answered, \u2018Who are you, Lord?\u2019 He said to me, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018I am Isa of Nazareth, whom you\npersecute.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 22:9"}, "\u201cThose who were with me indeed saw the light and were afraid, but they didn\u2019t understand the voice of him who spoke to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 22:10"}, "I said, \u2018What shall I do, Lord?\u2019 The Lord said to me, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Arise, and go into Damascus. There you will be told about all\nthings which are appointed for you to do.\u2019"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 22:11"}, "When I couldn\u2019t see for the glory of that light, being led by the hand of those who were with me, I came into Damascus.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 22:12"}, "One Ananias, a devout man according to the law, well reported of by all the Jews who lived in Damascus,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 22:13"}, "came to me, and standing by me said to me, \u2018Brother Saul, receive your sight!\u2019 In that very hour I looked up at him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 22:14"}, "He said, \u2018The Allah of our fathers has appointed you to know his will, and to see the Righteous One, and to hear a voice\nfrom his mouth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 22:15"}, "For you will be a witness for him to all men of what you have seen and heard.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 22:16"}, "Now why do you wait? Arise, be baptised, and wash away your sins, calling on the name of the Lord.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 22:17"}, "\u201cWhen I had returned to Jerusalem, and while I prayed in the temple, I fell into a trance,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 22:18"}, "and saw him saying to me, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Hurry and get out of Jerusalem quickly, because they will not receive testimony concerning\nme from you.\u2019"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 22:19"}, "I said, \u2018Lord, they themselves know that I imprisoned and beat in every synagogue those who believed in you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 22:20"}, "When the blood of Stephen, your witness, was shed, I also was standing by, consenting to his death, and guarding the\ncloaks of those who killed him.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 22:21"}, "\u201cHe said to me, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Depart, for I will send you out far from here to the\nGentiles.\u2019"]}, "\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 22:22"}, "They listened to him until he said that; then they lifted up their voice and said, \u201cRid the earth of this fellow, for he\nisn\u2019t fit to live!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 22:23"}, "As they cried out, threw off their cloaks, and threw dust into the air,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 22:24"}, "the commanding officer commanded him to be brought into the barracks, ordering him to be examined by scourging, that he\nmight know for what crime they shouted against him like that. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 22:25"}, "When they had tied him up with thongs, Paul asked the centurion who stood by, \u201cIs it lawful for you to scourge a man who\nis a Roman, and not found guilty?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 22:26"}, "When the centurion heard it, he went to the commanding officer and told him, \u201cWatch what you are about to do, for this\nman is a Roman!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 22:27"}, "The commanding officer came and asked him, \u201cTell me, are you a Roman?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cYes.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 22:28"}, "The commanding officer answered, \u201cI bought my citizenship for a great price.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Paul said, \u201cBut I was born a Roman.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 22:29"}, "Immediately those who were about to examine him departed from him, and the commanding officer also was afraid when he\nrealised that he was a Roman, because he had bound him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 22:30"}, "But on the next day, desiring to know the truth about why he was accused by the Jews, he freed him from the bonds, and\ncommanded the chief priests and all the council to come together, and brought Paul down and set him before them.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 23:1"}, "Paul, looking steadfastly at the council, said, \u201cBrothers, I have lived before Allah in all good conscience until today.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 23:2"}, "The high priest, Ananias, commanded those who stood by him to strike him on the mouth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 23:3"}, "Then Paul said to him, \u201cAllah will strike you, you whitewashed wall! Do you sit to judge me according to the law, and\ncommand me to be struck contrary to the law?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 23:4"}, "Those who stood by said, \u201cDo you malign Allah\u2019s high priest?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 23:5"}, "Paul said, \u201cI didn\u2019t know, brothers, that he was high priest. For it is written, \u2018You shall not speak evil of a ruler of\nyour people.\u2019\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["23:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 22:28"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 23:6"}, "But when Paul perceived that the one part were Sadducees and the other Pharisees, he cried out in the council, \u201cMen and\nbrothers, I am a Pharisee, a son of Pharisees. Concerning the hope and resurrection of the dead I am being judged!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 23:7"}, "When he had said this, an argument arose between the Pharisees and Sadducees, and the crowd was divided.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 23:8"}, "For the Sadducees say that there is no resurrection, nor angel, nor spirit; but the Pharisees confess all of these.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 23:9"}, "A great clamour arose, and some of the scribes of the Pharisees\u2019 part stood up, and contended, saying, \u201cWe find no evil in\nthis man. But if a spirit or angel has spoken to him, let\u2019s not fight against Allah!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 23:10"}, "When a great argument arose, the commanding officer, fearing that Paul would be torn in pieces by them, commanded the\nsoldiers to go down and take him by force from amongst them, and bring him into the barracks.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 23:11"}, "The following night, the Lord stood by him and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCheer up, Paul, for as you have testified about me at\nJerusalem, so you must testify also at Rome.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 23:12"}, "When it was day, some of the Jews banded together, and bound themselves under a curse, saying that they would neither eat\nnor drink until they had killed Paul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 23:13"}, "There were more than forty people who had made this conspiracy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 23:14"}, "They came to the chief priests and the elders, and said, \u201cWe have bound ourselves under a great curse to taste nothing\nuntil we have killed Paul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 23:15"}, "Now therefore, you with the council inform the commanding officer that he should bring him down to you tomorrow, as\nthough you were going to judge his case more exactly. We are ready to kill him before he comes near.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 23:16"}, "But Paul\u2019s sister\u2019s son heard they were lying in wait, and he came and entered into the barracks and told Paul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 23:17"}, "Paul summoned one of the centurions, and said, \u201cBring this young man to the commanding officer, for he has something to\ntell him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 23:18"}, "So he took him, and brought him to the commanding officer, and said, \u201cPaul, the prisoner, summoned me and asked me to\nbring this young man to you. He has something to tell you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 23:19"}, "The commanding officer took him by the hand, and going aside, asked him privately, \u201cWhat is it that you have to tell me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 23:20"}, "He said, \u201cThe Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul down to the council tomorrow, as though intending to enquire\nsomewhat more accurately concerning him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 23:21"}, "Therefore don\u2019t yield to them, for more than forty men lie in wait for him, who have bound themselves under a curse to\nneither eat nor drink until they have killed him. Now they are ready, looking for the promise from you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 23:22"}, "So the commanding officer let the young man go, charging him, \u201cTell no one that you have revealed these things to me.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 23:23"}, "He called to himself two of the centurions, and said, \u201cPrepare two hundred soldiers to go as far as Caesarea, with\nseventy horsemen, and two hundred men armed with spears, at the third hour of the\nnight.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["about 9:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 23:24"}, "He asked them to provide animals, that they might set Paul on one, and bring him safely to Felix the governor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 23:25"}, "He wrote a letter like this: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 23:26"}, "\u201cClaudius Lysias to the most excellent governor Felix: Greetings.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 23:27"}, "\u201cThis man was seized by the Jews, and was about to be killed by them, when I came with the soldiers and rescued him,\nhaving learnt that he was a Roman. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 23:28"}, "Desiring to know the cause why they accused him, I brought him down to their council.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 23:29"}, "I found him to be accused about questions of their law, but not to be charged with anything worthy of death or of\nimprisonment. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 23:30"}, "When I was told that the Jews lay in wait for the man, I sent him to you immediately, charging his accusers also to bring\ntheir accusations against him before you. Farewell.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 23:31"}, "So the soldiers, carrying out their orders, took Paul and brought him by night to Antipatris.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 23:32"}, "But on the next day they left the horsemen to go with him, and returned to the barracks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 23:33"}, "When they came to Caesarea and delivered the letter to the governor, they also presented Paul to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 23:34"}, "When the governor had read it, he asked what province he was from. When he understood that he was from Cilicia, he said,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 23:35"}, "\u201cI will hear you fully when your accusers also arrive.\u201d He commanded that he be kept in Herod\u2019s palace.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 24:1"}, "After five days, the high priest, Ananias, came down with certain elders and an orator, one Tertullus. They informed the\ngovernor against Paul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 24:2"}, "When he was called, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying, \u201cSeeing that by you we enjoy much peace, and that prosperity is\ncoming to this nation by your foresight, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 24:3"}, "we accept it in all ways and in all places, most excellent Felix, with all thankfulness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 24:4"}, "But that I don\u2019t delay you, I entreat you to bear with us and hear a few words.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 24:5"}, "For we have found this man to be a plague, an instigator of insurrections amongst all the Jews throughout the world, and a\nringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 24:6"}, "He even tried to profane the temple, and we arrested him.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cWe wanted to judge him according to our law,\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 24:7"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cbut the commanding officer, Lysias, came by and with great violence took him out of our\nhands,\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 24:8"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201ccommanding his accusers to come to\nyou.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "By examining him yourself you may ascertain all these things of which we accuse him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 24:9"}, "The Jews also joined in the attack, affirming that these things were so.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 24:10"}, "When the governor had beckoned to him to speak, Paul answered, \u201cBecause I know that you have been a judge of this nation\nfor many years, I cheerfully make my defence, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 24:11"}, "seeing that you can verify that it is not more than twelve days since I went up to worship at Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 24:12"}, "In the temple they didn\u2019t find me disputing with anyone or stirring up a crowd, either in the synagogues, or in the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 24:13"}, "Nor can they prove to you the things of which they now accuse me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 24:14"}, "But this I confess to you, that after the Way, which they call a sect, so I serve Allah of our fathers, believing all\nthings which are according to the law, and which are written in the prophets;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 24:15"}, "having hope towards Allah, which these also themselves look for, that there will be a resurrection of the dead, both of\nthe just and unjust. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 24:16"}, "In this I also practise always having a conscience void of offence towards Allah and men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 24:17"}, "Now after some years, I came to bring gifts for the needy to my nation, and offerings;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 24:18"}, "amid which certain Jews from Asia found me purified in the temple, not with a mob, nor with turmoil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 24:19"}, "They ought to have been here before you, and to make accusation, if they had anything against me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 24:20"}, "Or else let these men themselves say what injustice they found in me when I stood before the council,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 24:21"}, "unless it is for this one thing that I cried standing amongst them, \u2018Concerning the resurrection of the dead I am being\njudged before you today!\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 24:22"}, "But Felix, having more exact knowledge concerning the Way, deferred them, saying, \u201cWhen Lysias, the commanding officer,\ncomes down, I will decide your case.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 24:23"}, "He ordered the centurion that Paul should be kept in custody, and should have some privileges, and not to forbid any of\nhis friends to serve him or to visit him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 24:24"}, "But after some days, Felix came with Drusilla, his wife, who was a Jewess, and sent for Paul, and heard him concerning\nthe faith in Masih Isa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 24:25"}, "As he reasoned about righteousness, self-control, and the judgement to come, Felix was terrified, and answered, \u201cGo your\nway for this time, and when it is convenient for me, I will summon you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 24:26"}, "Meanwhile, he also hoped that money would be given to him by Paul, that he might release him. Therefore also he sent for\nhim more often and talked with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 24:27"}, "But when two years were fulfilled, Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus, and desiring to gain favour with the Jews,\nFelix left Paul in bonds. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 25:1"}, "Festus therefore, having come into the province, after three days went up to Jerusalem from Caesarea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 25:2"}, "Then the high priest and the principal men of the Jews informed him against Paul, and they begged him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 25:3"}, "asking a favour against him, that he would summon him to Jerusalem; plotting to kill him on the way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 25:4"}, "However Festus answered that Paul should be kept in custody at Caesarea, and that he himself was about to depart shortly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 25:5"}, "\u201cLet them therefore\u201d, he said, \u201cthat are in power amongst you go down with me, and if there is anything wrong in the man,\nlet them accuse him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 25:6"}, "When he had stayed amongst them more than ten days, he went down to Caesarea, and on the next day he sat on the judgement\nseat, and commanded Paul to be brought. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 25:7"}, "When he had come, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood around him, bringing against him many and grievous\ncharges which they could not prove, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 25:8"}, "while he said in his defence, \u201cNeither against the law of the Jews, nor against the temple, nor against Caesar, have I\nsinned at all.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 25:9"}, "But Festus, desiring to gain favour with the Jews, answered Paul and said, \u201cAre you willing to go up to Jerusalem, and be\njudged by me there concerning these things?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 25:10"}, "But Paul said, \u201cI am standing before Caesar\u2019s judgement seat, where I ought to be tried. I have done no wrong to the\nJews, as you also know very well. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 25:11"}, "For if I have done wrong and have committed anything worthy of death, I don\u2019t refuse to die; but if none of those things\nis true that they accuse me of, no one can give me up to them. I appeal to Caesar!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 25:12"}, "Then Festus, when he had conferred with the council, answered, \u201cYou have appealed to Caesar. To Caesar you shall go.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 25:13"}, "Now when some days had passed, King Agrippa and Bernice arrived at Caesarea, and greeted Festus.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 25:14"}, "As he stayed there many days, Festus laid Paul\u2019s case before the king, saying, \u201cThere is a certain man left a prisoner by\nFelix; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 25:15"}, "about whom, when I was at Jerusalem, the chief priests and the elders of the Jews informed me, asking for a sentence\nagainst him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 25:16"}, "I answered them that it is not the custom of the Romans to give up any man to destruction before the accused has met the\naccusers face to face and has had opportunity to make his defence concerning the matter laid against him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 25:17"}, "When therefore they had come together here, I didn\u2019t delay, but on the next day sat on the judgement seat and commanded\nthe man to be brought. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 25:18"}, "When the accusers stood up, they brought no charges against him of such things as I supposed;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 25:19"}, "but had certain questions against him about their own religion, and about one Isa, who was dead, whom Paul affirmed to be\nalive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 25:20"}, "Being perplexed how to enquire concerning these things, I asked whether he was willing to go to Jerusalem and there be\njudged concerning these matters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 25:21"}, "But when Paul had appealed to be kept for the decision of the emperor, I commanded him to be kept until I could send him\nto Caesar.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 25:22"}, "Agrippa said to Festus, \u201cI also would like to hear the man myself.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cTomorrow,\u201d he said, \u201cyou shall hear him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 25:23"}, "So on the next day, when Agrippa and Bernice had come with great pomp, and they had entered into the place of hearing\nwith the commanding officers and the principal men of the city, at the command of Festus, Paul was brought in.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 25:24"}, "Festus said, \u201cKing Agrippa, and all men who are here present with us, you see this man about whom all the multitude of\nthe Jews petitioned me, both at Jerusalem and here, crying that he ought not to live any longer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 25:25"}, "But when I found that he had committed nothing worthy of death, and as he himself appealed to the emperor I determined to\nsend him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 25:26"}, "of whom I have no certain thing to write to my lord. Therefore I have brought him out before you, and especially before\nyou, King Agrippa, that, after examination, I may have something to write.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 25:27"}, "For it seems to me unreasonable, in sending a prisoner, not to also specify the charges against him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 26:1"}, "Agrippa said to Paul, \u201cYou may speak for yourself.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Paul stretched out his hand, and made his defence. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 26:2"}, "\u201cI think myself happy, King Agrippa, that I am to make my defence before you today concerning all the things that I am\naccused by the Jews, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 26:3"}, "especially because you are expert in all customs and questions which are amongst the Jews. Therefore I beg you to hear me\npatiently. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 26:4"}, "\u201cIndeed, all the Jews know my way of life from my youth up, which was from the beginning amongst my own nation and at\nJerusalem; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 26:5"}, "having known me from the first, if they are willing to testify, that after the strictest sect of our religion I lived a\nPharisee. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 26:6"}, "Now I stand here to be judged for the hope of the promise made by Allah to our fathers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 26:7"}, "which our twelve tribes, earnestly serving night and day, hope to attain. Concerning this hope I am accused by the Jews,\nKing Agrippa! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 26:8"}, "Why is it judged incredible with you, if Allah does raise the dead?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 26:9"}, "\u201cI myself most certainly thought that I ought to do many things contrary to the name of Isa of Nazareth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 26:10"}, "I also did this in Jerusalem. I both shut up many of the saints in prisons, having received authority from the chief\npriests, and when they were put to death I gave my vote against them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 26:11"}, "Punishing them often in all the synagogues, I tried to make them blaspheme. Being exceedingly enraged against them, I\npersecuted them even to foreign cities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 26:12"}, "\u201cWhereupon as I travelled to Damascus with the authority and commission from the chief priests,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 26:13"}, "at noon, O king, I saw on the way a light from the sky, brighter than the sun, shining around me and those who travelled\nwith me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 26:14"}, "When we had all fallen to the earth, I heard a voice saying to me in the Hebrew language,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me? It is hard for you to kick against the\ngoads.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 26:15"}, "\u201cI said, \u2018Who are you, Lord?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cHe said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018I am Isa, whom you are persecuting. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 26:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But arise, and stand on your feet, for I have appeared to you for this purpose: to appoint you a servant and a\nwitness both of the things which you have seen, and of the things which I will reveal to you;\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 26:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["delivering you from the people, and from the Gentiles, to whom I send you,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 26:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["to open their eyes, that they may turn from darkness to light and from the power of Iblis to Allah, that they may\nreceive remission of sins and an inheritance amongst those who are sanctified by faith in\nme.\u2019"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 26:19"}, "\u201cTherefore, King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 26:20"}, "but declared first to them of Damascus, at Jerusalem, and throughout all the country of Judea, and also to the Gentiles,\nthat they should repent and turn to Allah, doing works worthy of repentance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 26:21"}, "For this reason the Jews seized me in the temple and tried to kill me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 26:22"}, "Having therefore obtained the help that is from Allah, I stand to this day testifying both to small and great, saying\nnothing but what the prophets and Musa said would happen, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 26:23"}, "how the Masih must suffer, and how, by the resurrection of the dead, he would be first to proclaim light both to these\npeople and to the Gentiles.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 26:24"}, "As he thus made his defence, Festus said with a loud voice, \u201cPaul, you are crazy! Your great learning is driving you\ninsane!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 26:25"}, "But he said, \u201cI am not crazy, most excellent Festus, but boldly declare words of truth and reasonableness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 26:26"}, "For the king knows of these things, to whom also I speak freely. For I am persuaded that none of these things is hidden\nfrom him, for this has not been done in a corner. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 26:27"}, "King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know that you believe.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 26:28"}, "Agrippa said to Paul, \u201cWith a little persuasion are you trying to make me a Christian?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 26:29"}, "Paul said, \u201cI pray to Allah, that whether with little or with much, not only you, but also all that hear me today, might\nbecome such as I am, except for these bonds.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 26:30"}, "The king rose up with the governor, and Bernice, and those who sat with them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 26:31"}, "When they had withdrawn, they spoke to one another, saying, \u201cThis man does nothing worthy of death or of bonds.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 26:32"}, "Agrippa said to Festus, \u201cThis man might have been set free if he had not appealed to Caesar.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 27:1"}, "When it was determined that we should sail for Italy, they delivered Paul and certain other prisoners to a centurion named\nJulius, of the Augustan band. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 27:2"}, "Embarking in a ship of Adramyttium, which was about to sail to places on the coast of Asia, we put to sea, Aristarchus, a\nMacedonian of Thessalonica, being with us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 27:3"}, "The next day, we touched at Sidon. Julius treated Paul kindly, and gave him permission to go to his friends and refresh\nhimself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 27:4"}, "Putting to sea from there, we sailed under the lee of Cyprus, because the winds were contrary.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 27:5"}, "When we had sailed across the sea which is off Cilicia and Pamphylia, we came to Myra, a city of Lycia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 27:6"}, "There the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing for Italy, and he put us on board.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 27:7"}, "When we had sailed slowly many days, and had come with difficulty opposite Cnidus, the wind not allowing us further, we\nsailed under the lee of Crete, opposite Salmone. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 27:8"}, "With difficulty sailing along it we came to a certain place called Fair Havens, near the city of Lasea.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 27:9"}, "When much time had passed and the voyage was now dangerous, because the Fast had now already gone by, Paul admonished them\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 27:10"}, "and said to them, \u201cSirs, I perceive that the voyage will be with injury and much loss, not only of the cargo and the\nship, but also of our lives.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 27:11"}, "But the centurion gave more heed to the master and to the owner of the ship than to those things which were spoken by\nPaul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 27:12"}, "Because the haven was not suitable to winter in, the majority advised going to sea from there, if by any means they could\nreach Phoenix, and winter there, which is a port of Crete, looking southwest and northwest.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 27:13"}, "When the south wind blew softly, supposing that they had obtained their purpose, they weighed anchor and sailed along\nCrete, close to shore. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 27:14"}, "But before long, a stormy wind beat down from shore, which is called Euroclydon.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Or, \u201ca northeaster\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 27:15"}, "When the ship was caught and couldn\u2019t face the wind, we gave way to it and were driven along.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 27:16"}, "Running under the lee of a small island called Clauda, we were able, with difficulty, to secure the boat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 27:17"}, "After they had hoisted it up, they used cables to help reinforce the ship. Fearing that they would run aground on the\nSyrtis sand bars, they lowered the sea anchor, and so were driven along.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 27:18"}, "As we laboured exceedingly with the storm, the next day they began to throw things overboard.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 27:19"}, "On the third day, they threw out the ship\u2019s tackle with their own hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 27:20"}, "When neither sun nor stars shone on us for many days, and no small storm pressed on us, all hope that we would be saved\nwas now taken away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 27:21"}, "When they had been long without food, Paul stood up in the middle of them, and said, \u201cSirs, you should have listened to\nme, and not have set sail from Crete and have gotten this injury and loss.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 27:22"}, "Now I exhort you to cheer up, for there will be no loss of life amongst you, but only of the ship.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 27:23"}, "For there stood by me this night an angel, belonging to Allah whose I am and whom I serve,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 27:24"}, "saying, \u2018Don\u2019t be afraid, Paul. You must stand before Caesar. Behold, Allah has granted you all those who sail with you.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 27:25"}, "Therefore, sirs, cheer up! For I believe Allah, that it will be just as it has been spoken to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 27:26"}, "But we must run aground on a certain island.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 27:27"}, "But when the fourteenth night had come, as we were driven back and forth in the Adriatic Sea, about midnight the sailors\nsurmised that they were drawing near to some land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 27:28"}, "They took soundings, and found twenty fathoms.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:28\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["20 fathoms = 120 feet = 36.6 metres"]}], "caller": "+"}, " After a little while, they took soundings again, and found fifteen\nfathoms.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["15 fathoms = 90 feet = 27.4 metres"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 27:29"}, "Fearing that we would run aground on rocky ground, they let go four anchors from the stern, and wished for daylight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 27:30"}, "As the sailors were trying to flee out of the ship, and had lowered the boat into the sea, pretending that they would lay\nout anchors from the bow, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 27:31"}, "Paul said to the centurion and to the soldiers, \u201cUnless these stay in the ship, you can\u2019t be saved.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ACT 27:32"}, "Then the soldiers cut away the ropes of the boat, and let it fall off.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ACT 27:33"}, "While the day was coming on, Paul begged them all to take some food, saying, \u201cToday is the fourteenth day that you wait\nand continue fasting, having taken nothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ACT 27:34"}, "Therefore I beg you to take some food; for this is for your safety; for not a hair will perish from any of your heads.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ACT 27:35"}, "When he had said this, and had taken bread, he gave thanks to Allah in the presence of all, then he broke it and began to\neat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ACT 27:36"}, "Then they all cheered up, and they also took food. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ACT 27:37"}, "In all, we were two hundred and seventy-six souls on the ship.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ACT 27:38"}, "When they had eaten enough, they lightened the ship, throwing out the wheat into the sea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "ACT 27:39"}, "When it was day, they didn\u2019t recognise the land, but they noticed a certain bay with a beach, and they decided to try to\ndrive the ship onto it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "ACT 27:40"}, "Casting off the anchors, they left them in the sea, at the same time untying the rudder ropes. Hoisting up the foresail\nto the wind, they made for the beach. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "ACT 27:41"}, "But coming to a place where two seas met, they ran the vessel aground. The bow struck and remained immovable, but the\nstern began to break up by the violence of the waves. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "ACT 27:42"}, "The soldiers\u2019 counsel was to kill the prisoners, so that none of them would swim out and escape.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "ACT 27:43"}, "But the centurion, desiring to save Paul, stopped them from their purpose, and commanded that those who could swim should\nthrow themselves overboard first to go towards the land; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "ACT 27:44"}, "and the rest should follow, some on planks, and some on other things from the ship. So they all escaped safely to the\nland. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ACT 28:1"}, "When we had escaped, then they", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201cwe\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " learnt that the island was called Malta.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ACT 28:2"}, "The natives showed us uncommon kindness; for they kindled a fire and received us all, because of the present rain and\nbecause of the cold. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ACT 28:3"}, "But when Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks and laid them on the fire, a viper came out because of the heat, and\nfastened on his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ACT 28:4"}, "When the natives saw the creature hanging from his hand, they said to one another, \u201cNo doubt this man is a murderer, whom,\nthough he has escaped from the sea, yet Justice has not allowed to live.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ACT 28:5"}, "However he shook off the creature into the fire, and wasn\u2019t harmed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ACT 28:6"}, "But they expected that he would have swollen or fallen down dead suddenly, but when they watched for a long time and saw\nnothing bad happen to him, they changed their minds, and said that he was a god.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ACT 28:7"}, "Now in the neighbourhood of that place were lands belonging to the chief man of the island, named Publius, who received\nus, and courteously entertained us for three days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ACT 28:8"}, "The father of Publius lay sick of fever and dysentery. Paul entered in to him, prayed, and laying his hands on him, healed\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ACT 28:9"}, "Then when this was done, the rest also who had diseases in the island came and were cured.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ACT 28:10"}, "They also honoured us with many honours, and when we sailed, they put on board the things that we needed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ACT 28:11"}, "After three months, we set sail in a ship of Alexandria which had wintered in the island, whose sign was \u201cThe Twin\nBrothers.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ACT 28:12"}, "Touching at Syracuse, we stayed there three days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ACT 28:13"}, "From there we circled around and arrived at Rhegium. After one day, a south wind sprang up, and on the second day we came\nto Puteoli, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ACT 28:14"}, "where we found brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and were entreated to stay with them for seven days. So we came to Rome.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ACT 28:15"}, "From there the brothers, when they heard of us, came to meet us as far as The Market of Appius and The Three Taverns.\nWhen Paul saw them, he thanked Allah and took courage. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ACT 28:16"}, "When we entered into Rome, the centurion delivered the prisoners to the captain of the guard, but Paul was allowed to\nstay by himself with the soldier who guarded him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ACT 28:17"}, "After three days Paul called together those who were the leaders of the Jews. When they had come together, he said to\nthem, \u201cI, brothers, though I had done nothing against the people or the customs of our fathers, still was delivered prisoner\nfrom Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ACT 28:18"}, "who, when they had examined me, desired to set me free, because there was no cause of death in me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ACT 28:19"}, "But when the Jews spoke against it, I was constrained to appeal to Caesar, not that I had anything about which to accuse\nmy nation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ACT 28:20"}, "For this cause therefore I asked to see you and to speak with you. For because of the hope of Israel I am bound with this\nchain.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ACT 28:21"}, "They said to him, \u201cWe neither received letters from Judea concerning you, nor did any of the brothers come here and\nreport or speak any evil of you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ACT 28:22"}, "But we desire to hear from you what you think. For, as concerning this sect, it is known to us that everywhere it is\nspoken against.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ACT 28:23"}, "When they had appointed him a day, many people came to him at his lodging. He explained to them, testifying about Allah\u2019s\nKingdom, and persuading them concerning Isa, both from the law of Musa and from the prophets, from morning until evening.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ACT 28:24"}, "Some believed the things which were spoken, and some disbelieved.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ACT 28:25"}, "When they didn\u2019t agree amongst themselves, they departed after Paul had spoken one word, \u201cThe Holy Spirit spoke rightly\nthrough Isaiah the prophet to our fathers, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ACT 28:26"}, "saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Go to this people and say, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["in hearing, you will hear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but will in no way understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["In seeing, you will see, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but will in no way perceive. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ACT 28:27"}, "For this people\u2019s heart has grown callous. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their ears are dull of hearing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their eyes they have closed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Lest they should see with their eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["hear with their ears, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["understand with their heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and would turn again, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["then I would heal them.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["28:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 6:9-10"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ACT 28:28"}, "\u201cBe it known therefore to you, that the salvation of Allah is sent to the nations, and they will listen.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ACT 28:29"}, "When he had said these words, the Jews departed, having a great dispute amongst\nthemselves.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 29."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ACT 28:30"}, "Paul stayed two whole years in his own rented house and received all who were coming to him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ACT 28:31"}, "preaching Allah\u2019s Kingdom, and teaching the things concerning the Lord Al Masih Isa with all boldness, without hindrance.\n"]}]}